1
00:00:01,160 --> 00:00:02,595
Aren't you cold?
You're wearing that again.

2
00:00:02,595 --> 00:00:04,697
- I'm fine.
- You are?

3
00:00:04,697 --> 00:00:06,566
It's just, earlier,

4
00:00:06,566 --> 00:00:08,030
right after the women's introductions...

5
00:00:08,114 --> 00:00:08,917
Yes.

6
00:00:09,001 --> 00:00:14,340
they told the mothers to place their sons
by the woman they liked.

7
00:00:15,341 --> 00:00:18,278
- Hello.
- Hello.

8
00:00:18,278 --> 00:00:20,747
(In Kwon's mother chose Jeong Yoon
in the mothers' vote.)

9
00:00:21,114 --> 00:00:25,885
There was a reason
we had to make that choice.

10
00:00:25,885 --> 00:00:28,087
You'll find out tomorrow,

11
00:00:28,087 --> 00:00:31,124
but I wanted to let you know in advance.

12
00:00:32,058 --> 00:00:34,427
Can I try to guess what it might be?

13
00:00:34,427 --> 00:00:36,696
But I can't answer you.

14
00:00:36,696 --> 00:00:38,865
So even if you guess,
I can't give anything away.

15
00:00:40,500 --> 00:00:44,270
You seem like you'd be
quite a bit older than me.

16
00:00:44,270 --> 00:00:45,672
Do I look that old?

17
00:00:45,672 --> 00:00:46,906
No.

18
00:00:47,240 --> 00:00:49,809
It's the way you speak.

19
00:00:49,809 --> 00:00:52,779
You sound like an older guy.

20
00:00:54,714 --> 00:00:58,251
So, did you eat the boxed lunch earlier?

21
00:00:58,251 --> 00:00:59,085
Yes.

22
00:00:59,085 --> 00:01:00,920
- Sorry.
- It was delicious, though.

23
00:01:02,021 --> 00:01:03,623
My mom and I really enjoyed it.

24
00:01:04,123 --> 00:01:06,059
It seems like you feel sorry about that.

25
00:01:06,059 --> 00:01:09,162
- Thanks for coming to see me.
- Of course.

26
00:01:09,362 --> 00:01:11,731
It's nothing much, really.

27
00:01:11,731 --> 00:01:13,032
I thought you might be tired today.

28
00:01:13,032 --> 00:01:13,833
Really?

29
00:01:13,833 --> 00:01:15,802
- Have one each with your mother.
- Thank you.

30
00:01:16,502 --> 00:01:17,503
What is it?

31
00:01:17,503 --> 00:01:18,972
(Vitamins)

32
00:01:18,972 --> 00:01:21,174
Vitamins.

33
00:01:21,174 --> 00:01:24,477
- Those are good.
- Those are always nice.

34
00:01:24,477 --> 00:01:25,511
We should learn from him.

35
00:01:25,511 --> 00:01:27,213
Did you bring those
all the way from Seoul?

36
00:01:27,213 --> 00:01:28,514
Yes, one for my mom too.

37
00:01:29,415 --> 00:01:30,850
I brought them to have with her.

38
00:01:30,850 --> 00:01:33,253
I'm touched. I was exhausted today.

39
00:01:35,688 --> 00:01:37,257
But...

40
00:01:37,257 --> 00:01:41,027
I wish In Kwon were...

41
00:01:41,027 --> 00:01:44,197
a little warmer in how he speaks and acts.

42
00:01:44,197 --> 00:01:45,632
He's kind of a testosterone-driven type.

43
00:01:45,632 --> 00:01:47,901
He's very T-type, isn't he?

44
00:01:47,901 --> 00:01:50,436
He has a very testosterone-driven,
very T-type personality,

45
00:01:50,436 --> 00:01:53,206
so I'm not sure how much this will help.

46
00:01:54,507 --> 00:01:56,109
Mom, he gave me this.

47
00:01:57,010 --> 00:01:58,311
In Kwon did.

48
00:01:58,311 --> 00:01:59,712
He said they're for us.

49
00:01:59,712 --> 00:02:00,513
Why?

50
00:02:00,513 --> 00:02:03,616
He said there was a reason...

51
00:02:03,616 --> 00:02:05,718
he had to make that choice
and couldn't choose me,

52
00:02:05,718 --> 00:02:07,820
because he hadn't introduced himself yet.

53
00:02:07,820 --> 00:02:08,788
Then he gave me this.

54
00:02:09,455 --> 00:02:11,224
He gave me one for you too.

55
00:02:11,224 --> 00:02:12,091
(Squeals)

56
00:02:12,091 --> 00:02:13,226
They're only vitamins.

57
00:02:13,226 --> 00:02:14,994
Honestly, I was feeling a little sad.

58
00:02:14,994 --> 00:02:15,828
His timing was good.

59
00:02:15,828 --> 00:02:17,630
The person I'm most interested in now...

60
00:02:17,630 --> 00:02:21,267
is Lee In Kwon, who showed his interest...

61
00:02:21,267 --> 00:02:22,635
by giving me vitamins.

62
00:02:22,635 --> 00:02:25,371
Kwon Ye Chan is my second choice.

63
00:02:25,371 --> 00:02:28,107
It made me think, "He was thinking of me."

64
00:02:28,107 --> 00:02:29,409
It made my heart flutter a little.

65
00:02:30,910 --> 00:02:31,811
Vitamin flirting.

66
00:02:31,811 --> 00:02:32,812
She really is young.

67
00:02:32,812 --> 00:02:35,148
One vitamin, and she's already swayed.

68
00:02:35,148 --> 00:02:37,750
- The vitamin flirt worked.
- That's not the point.

69
00:02:37,750 --> 00:02:40,987
Do Yoon got zero votes from the mothers.

70
00:02:40,987 --> 00:02:43,623
That left her feeling really empty.

71
00:02:43,623 --> 00:02:44,557
That's right.

72
00:02:44,557 --> 00:02:46,893
Then he came over and gave her that.

73
00:02:46,893 --> 00:02:49,028
- And he shot straight to first place.
- Of course.

74
00:02:50,763 --> 00:02:52,165
(Day 3 dawns, and the men's credentials
will be revealed.)

75
00:02:52,165 --> 00:02:54,767
It's the morning of Day Three.

76
00:02:55,668 --> 00:02:56,636
Today, at last...

77
00:02:58,371 --> 00:03:00,573
(Shin Woo)

78
00:03:01,641 --> 00:03:03,042
(Moisturizing the moment he wakes up)

79
00:03:03,042 --> 00:03:04,043
He's putting on a sheet mask.

80
00:03:07,113 --> 00:03:08,615
Mom.

81
00:03:08,615 --> 00:03:12,218
You don't have any conditioner
or hair serum, do you?

82
00:03:12,218 --> 00:03:12,886
No.

83
00:03:13,386 --> 00:03:17,724
(The men's quarters are bustling
from early morning.)

84
00:03:18,591 --> 00:03:19,626
Your slacks.

85
00:03:20,493 --> 00:03:22,996
Ye Chan, aren't these yours?

86
00:03:22,996 --> 00:03:24,163
These, with the top...

87
00:03:25,265 --> 00:03:26,332
Goodness.

88
00:03:26,332 --> 00:03:28,835
(Complete chaos)

89
00:03:29,502 --> 00:03:31,638
It's finally our turn.

90
00:03:31,638 --> 00:03:32,405
The women's choice.

91
00:03:32,405 --> 00:03:35,375
I hope you finally get
your chance today, Kang Hyeon.

92
00:03:35,375 --> 00:03:36,743
Absolutely.

93
00:03:36,743 --> 00:03:39,345
But it'd be heartbreaking
if anyone got zero votes.

94
00:03:39,345 --> 00:03:41,114
I know what getting zero votes feels like.

95
00:03:41,114 --> 00:03:43,716
It felt awful.
There was nothing fun about it.

96
00:03:44,817 --> 00:03:46,953
It's so pretty over there.

97
00:03:46,953 --> 00:03:48,054
- It's beautiful.
- The sky?

98
00:03:48,054 --> 00:03:50,423
The blue sky and greenery
are so beautiful.

99
00:03:50,423 --> 00:03:51,391
They go perfectly together.

100
00:03:51,391 --> 00:03:53,259
(Everything looks beautiful to the mothers
and daughters this morning.)

101
00:03:53,426 --> 00:03:54,761
I'll stand up and read it.

102
00:03:55,195 --> 00:03:56,362
(The mothers and sons are still bustling.)

103
00:03:56,362 --> 00:03:58,531
I'm Kim Do Gyu, Kwon Ye Chan's mother.

104
00:03:58,531 --> 00:04:00,967
The mothers are practicing now.

105
00:04:00,967 --> 00:04:02,669
Eye contact! Don't forget eye contact.

106
00:04:02,669 --> 00:04:04,437
I should look up at them now and then.

107
00:04:04,437 --> 00:04:06,072
No matter which woman comes to him,

108
00:04:06,072 --> 00:04:08,508
I can confidently say
he'll always be there to protect her.

109
00:04:08,508 --> 00:04:09,442
Should we do it like this?

110
00:04:09,442 --> 00:04:10,743
"To protect her," like this?

111
00:04:10,743 --> 00:04:11,811
(A confident gesture)

112
00:04:11,811 --> 00:04:13,012
They're even choreographing it?

113
00:04:14,514 --> 00:04:16,216
Goodness.

114
00:04:16,216 --> 00:04:17,350
I need to calm down.

115
00:04:18,685 --> 00:04:19,652
You're nervous, aren't you?

116
00:04:19,652 --> 00:04:21,788
More than the introduction itself,

117
00:04:21,788 --> 00:04:23,089
I'm worried he won't be chosen.

118
00:04:23,990 --> 00:04:25,358
Could you please not
say things like that, ma'am?

119
00:04:26,192 --> 00:04:27,360
I can't keep anything down.

120
00:04:27,360 --> 00:04:30,230
I keep telling myself to let go,
but I don't think I can.

121
00:04:30,230 --> 00:04:31,364
Goodness.

122
00:04:32,098 --> 00:04:33,299
Take deep breaths from your diaphragm.

123
00:04:33,299 --> 00:04:34,067
Welcome.

124
00:04:34,067 --> 00:04:35,168
Hello.

125
00:04:35,768 --> 00:04:39,639
(They arrive at the introduction site
full of nerves.)

126
00:04:40,106 --> 00:04:41,875
Hello.

127
00:04:41,875 --> 00:04:42,976
Hello.

128
00:04:43,209 --> 00:04:45,378
Did Shin Woo wear glasses before?

129
00:04:45,378 --> 00:04:46,379
No, he didn't.

130
00:04:46,813 --> 00:04:47,780
I want to make a good impression.

131
00:04:48,948 --> 00:04:50,083
He looks like a gentleman.

132
00:04:51,417 --> 00:04:52,352
Hello.

133
00:04:53,086 --> 00:04:54,020
Hello.

134
00:04:56,890 --> 00:04:58,391
Look.

135
00:04:58,391 --> 00:05:00,493
The atmosphere here and over there
feels completely different.

136
00:05:01,494 --> 00:05:03,062
- We feel relieved.
- The air feels different.

137
00:05:03,062 --> 00:05:05,198
It feels really tense over here.

138
00:05:06,966 --> 00:05:09,569
Today, we'll have the men's introductions.

139
00:05:10,203 --> 00:05:11,404
Finally.

140
00:05:12,272 --> 00:05:14,974
I'm sure many are very curious.

141
00:05:14,974 --> 00:05:16,509
(More than anyone)

142
00:05:19,045 --> 00:05:22,282
The mothers will
introduce them again today.

143
00:05:23,383 --> 00:05:25,518
We'll begin with Lee In Kwon.

144
00:05:25,518 --> 00:05:26,553
They must be so nervous.

145
00:05:26,553 --> 00:05:28,288
Going second might be
even more nerve-racking.

146
00:05:29,522 --> 00:05:31,624
Going first must be the worst, right?

147
00:05:32,258 --> 00:05:33,426
I'm curious about his age.

148
00:05:34,794 --> 00:05:38,598
(The men's credentials
are finally revealed.)

149
00:05:38,598 --> 00:05:39,899
Hello.

150
00:05:39,899 --> 00:05:42,802
I'm Bae Myeong Ok, Lee In Kwon's mother.

151
00:05:42,802 --> 00:05:46,039
My son was born in 1990,

152
00:05:46,039 --> 00:05:48,041
so he's 37 years old this year.

153
00:05:49,409 --> 00:05:50,510
Nine years apart.

154
00:05:51,177 --> 00:05:52,745
That's quite a gap.

155
00:05:52,745 --> 00:05:55,448
He's nine years older than Do Yoon.

156
00:05:55,448 --> 00:05:56,749
He looks so young for his age.

157
00:05:56,749 --> 00:05:58,585
Mothers, by any chance,

158
00:05:58,585 --> 00:06:01,087
do you recognize his face?

159
00:06:01,087 --> 00:06:01,854
That's right.

160
00:06:01,854 --> 00:06:03,256
Yes.

161
00:06:03,256 --> 00:06:06,860
Or does his voice sound familiar?

162
00:06:06,860 --> 00:06:08,628
In Kwon currently works across...

163
00:06:08,628 --> 00:06:11,130
news and current affairs,

164
00:06:11,130 --> 00:06:14,133
radio, and sports broadcasting,

165
00:06:14,133 --> 00:06:15,835
among other fields.

166
00:06:15,835 --> 00:06:18,504
He has been an SBS announcer
for nine years.

167
00:06:23,309 --> 00:06:24,510
That's a great workplace.

168
00:06:25,879 --> 00:06:27,347
I knew I'd seen him somewhere.

169
00:06:28,214 --> 00:06:31,084
Coming up,
a café that gets hotter as it gets colder.

170
00:06:31,484 --> 00:06:35,722
We've received lots of stories
of testosterone-driven people.

171
00:06:35,855 --> 00:06:39,626
(An SBS announcer hired through
open recruitment, now in his ninth year)

172
00:06:39,626 --> 00:06:41,995
I told you I recognized him.

173
00:06:41,995 --> 00:06:45,665
If you do many SBS programs,
it's hard not to recognize him.

174
00:06:45,665 --> 00:06:48,668
When you walk into SBS headquarters,

175
00:06:48,668 --> 00:06:49,636
there's an ad.

176
00:06:49,636 --> 00:06:51,037
That's right.

177
00:06:51,037 --> 00:06:54,440
There's an ad for his FM radio show.

178
00:06:54,440 --> 00:06:56,776
And in the evening,

179
00:06:56,776 --> 00:06:58,278
"Live Today."

180
00:06:58,278 --> 00:07:01,748
He's been hosting "Live Today,"

181
00:07:01,748 --> 00:07:04,350
so many people have probably seen him.

182
00:07:04,851 --> 00:07:07,921
In Kwon graduated from Korea University.

183
00:07:07,921 --> 00:07:09,022
Before graduating,

184
00:07:10,290 --> 00:07:12,292
he passed the announcer exam...

185
00:07:12,292 --> 00:07:15,628
on his very first try.

186
00:07:17,230 --> 00:07:19,632
I don't know whom he gets his wit from,

187
00:07:19,632 --> 00:07:21,034
but he has a great way with words...

188
00:07:23,937 --> 00:07:25,538
and is absolutely hilarious.

189
00:07:26,806 --> 00:07:28,641
- That's true.
- That's true.

190
00:07:28,641 --> 00:07:30,877
As for In Kwon's ideal partner,

191
00:07:30,877 --> 00:07:34,047
In Kwon is very financially responsible.

192
00:07:34,047 --> 00:07:35,515
He seems to want someone
who's good with money,

193
00:07:35,515 --> 00:07:38,885
takes pride in her career,

194
00:07:38,885 --> 00:07:40,520
and can keep pace with him.

195
00:07:40,520 --> 00:07:43,022
That seems to be his type.

196
00:07:43,690 --> 00:07:47,193
I value what's on the inside.

197
00:07:47,193 --> 00:07:50,163
Someone with bright energy,

198
00:07:50,163 --> 00:07:52,599
someone I'd admire
even as my daughter-in-law.

199
00:07:53,466 --> 00:07:57,136
May just one such woman come to him today.

200
00:07:58,171 --> 00:07:59,639
That was perfect.

201
00:07:59,639 --> 00:08:00,640
She's good.

202
00:08:01,341 --> 00:08:02,876
- You did well.
- Did I?

203
00:08:03,810 --> 00:08:04,911
Please ask any questions you have.

204
00:08:04,911 --> 00:08:05,511
(Their hands shoot up.)

205
00:08:05,511 --> 00:08:06,446
You go first.

206
00:08:06,446 --> 00:08:09,515
What's the biggest age gap you'd consider?

207
00:08:10,516 --> 00:08:13,286
That was very direct.

208
00:08:13,286 --> 00:08:14,220
She's bold.

209
00:08:15,455 --> 00:08:18,691
I've always hoped...

210
00:08:18,691 --> 00:08:19,926
there wouldn't be too big an age gap.

211
00:08:20,860 --> 00:08:24,531
But if she doesn't mind either,

212
00:08:24,864 --> 00:08:27,634
I honestly haven't set...

213
00:08:27,634 --> 00:08:29,702
a specific limit in either direction.

214
00:08:29,702 --> 00:08:31,771
How many women have caught your interest?

215
00:08:32,472 --> 00:08:35,341
About two.

216
00:08:35,341 --> 00:08:38,278
Were you hired
through SBS's open recruitment?

217
00:08:38,278 --> 00:08:39,245
Yes, that's right.

218
00:08:39,245 --> 00:08:41,414
These days, many announcers...

219
00:08:41,414 --> 00:08:43,416
leave their networks and go freelance.

220
00:08:43,416 --> 00:08:44,651
(Gasp)

221
00:08:44,651 --> 00:08:46,119
That could be a sensitive question.

222
00:08:46,119 --> 00:08:47,353
Really?

223
00:08:47,353 --> 00:08:49,188
And we're on an SBS show.

224
00:08:50,390 --> 00:08:51,991
She struck a sensitive nerve.

225
00:08:53,726 --> 00:08:55,628
That was a very pointed question.

226
00:08:56,729 --> 00:08:58,031
I'm sorry.

227
00:08:58,031 --> 00:09:00,500
I was just asking
because I honestly didn't know.

228
00:09:01,167 --> 00:09:03,203
The CEO is watching.

229
00:09:06,072 --> 00:09:08,441
- To give you an honest answer,
- I'm sorry.

230
00:09:08,441 --> 00:09:11,778
there's still so much
I haven't done at SBS,

231
00:09:11,778 --> 00:09:14,847
and so many people
I still want to work with,

232
00:09:14,847 --> 00:09:17,483
so I haven't seriously considered it yet.

233
00:09:17,483 --> 00:09:18,851
Okay. I'm sorry.

234
00:09:21,120 --> 00:09:24,290
What are announcers' working hours...

235
00:09:24,290 --> 00:09:27,026
and daily schedules like?

236
00:09:27,026 --> 00:09:28,528
Their questions are sharp.

237
00:09:28,528 --> 00:09:31,698
I currently host a radio show...

238
00:09:32,432 --> 00:09:34,133
from 5 a.m. to 7 a.m.

239
00:09:34,667 --> 00:09:38,037
And from 6 p.m. to 7 p.m.,

240
00:09:38,037 --> 00:09:40,707
I host a current affairs show live.

241
00:09:40,707 --> 00:09:43,810
I go to bed early and get up early.

242
00:09:45,778 --> 00:09:46,713
What is...

243
00:09:46,713 --> 00:09:49,749
one thing you couldn't accept in a woman?

244
00:09:50,250 --> 00:09:52,151
Extravagant spending would be hard for me.

245
00:09:53,286 --> 00:09:57,357
Conversely, what's one quality...

246
00:09:57,357 --> 00:09:58,658
you'd definitely want her to have?

247
00:09:58,925 --> 00:10:00,960
I want her to be
on my side unconditionally.

248
00:10:00,960 --> 00:10:02,896
If I tell her...

249
00:10:02,896 --> 00:10:05,098
that A is B,

250
00:10:05,098 --> 00:10:07,000
even if it's actually C or D,

251
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:09,102
I want someone who'll believe me
without question.

252
00:10:09,736 --> 00:10:12,372
I want to be that person
for my partner too,

253
00:10:12,372 --> 00:10:14,574
so I hope she feels the same way about me.

254
00:10:15,108 --> 00:10:16,442
That concludes my introduction.

255
00:10:16,442 --> 00:10:19,045
(Lee In Kwon and his mother
conclude the introduction.)

256
00:10:19,045 --> 00:10:21,281
That closing was so impressive.

257
00:10:22,582 --> 00:10:24,717
After that introduction,

258
00:10:24,717 --> 00:10:27,654
I have a feeling
In Kwon's popularity is about to rise.

259
00:10:27,654 --> 00:10:29,155
- Yes, I think so too.
- Because...

260
00:10:29,155 --> 00:10:31,524
the mothers' reactions were very positive.

261
00:10:31,524 --> 00:10:32,425
They asked a lot of questions.

262
00:10:32,425 --> 00:10:34,961
And very detailed ones at that.

263
00:10:36,162 --> 00:10:36,996
(Kwon Ye Chan and his mother are next.)

264
00:10:36,996 --> 00:10:38,798
- It's Ye Chan's turn.
- Ye Chan.

265
00:10:38,798 --> 00:10:39,632
Stand beside me.

266
00:10:40,366 --> 00:10:42,001
- Hello.
- Hello, everyone.

267
00:10:44,604 --> 00:10:46,372
I am...

268
00:10:47,040 --> 00:10:48,041
Take your time.

269
00:10:48,341 --> 00:10:49,309
Hello.

270
00:10:49,309 --> 00:10:50,443
(She starts over.)

271
00:10:50,443 --> 00:10:52,612
She's so nervous.

272
00:10:52,845 --> 00:10:54,914
She must be shaking.

273
00:10:56,082 --> 00:10:58,985
I'm Kim Do Gyu, Kwon Ye Chan's mother.

274
00:10:59,485 --> 00:11:00,720
My son...

275
00:11:00,720 --> 00:11:04,691
was born in 1993 and is 34 years old.

276
00:11:05,225 --> 00:11:06,326
He's young.

277
00:11:06,826 --> 00:11:08,361
He's younger than I thought.

278
00:11:08,361 --> 00:11:11,397
He works as a voice actor.

279
00:11:11,397 --> 00:11:12,699
No, that was a joke.

280
00:11:14,968 --> 00:11:16,002
I thought he was a voice actor.

281
00:11:17,937 --> 00:11:19,939
He's a lawyer
in his third year of practice.

282
00:11:19,939 --> 00:11:21,107
I knew it.

283
00:11:21,107 --> 00:11:22,008
There it is.

284
00:11:22,675 --> 00:11:26,045
That's why he kept taking notes.

285
00:11:26,579 --> 00:11:27,614
He kept writing things down.

286
00:11:27,614 --> 00:11:30,450
I knew from the start
he had to be a licensed professional,

287
00:11:30,450 --> 00:11:33,887
like a lawyer or accountant.

288
00:11:33,887 --> 00:11:37,390
You can often tell
by the way someone speaks.

289
00:11:37,390 --> 00:11:38,424
A lawyer.

290
00:11:39,993 --> 00:11:41,094
They're taking notes, right?

291
00:11:41,628 --> 00:11:43,329
There's another licensed professional.

292
00:11:46,699 --> 00:11:47,700
I knew one would show up.

293
00:11:47,700 --> 00:11:51,337
He doesn't just solve
his clients' legal problems.

294
00:11:51,337 --> 00:11:55,008
He also has the heart
to help people in need.

295
00:11:55,708 --> 00:11:58,945
He once represented a teenager
from a struggling family...

296
00:11:58,945 --> 00:12:00,813
and brought the case
to a successful resolution.

297
00:12:00,813 --> 00:12:03,516
So last year,

298
00:12:03,516 --> 00:12:06,219
Ye Chan was prominently featured
in a major newspaper.

299
00:12:08,254 --> 00:12:12,091
All four years at Sungkyunkwan University,

300
00:12:12,091 --> 00:12:14,594
he attended on a full scholarship.

301
00:12:14,594 --> 00:12:17,597
He seems to achieve every goal he sets.

302
00:12:17,964 --> 00:12:20,867
He is 188 cm tall,

303
00:12:20,867 --> 00:12:23,303
and as you can see,

304
00:12:23,303 --> 00:12:25,038
he's reasonably good-looking.

305
00:12:25,038 --> 00:12:27,240
That's what he says.

306
00:12:27,240 --> 00:12:29,142
So that wasn't his mother's opinion.

307
00:12:29,142 --> 00:12:30,210
He is good-looking.

308
00:12:31,444 --> 00:12:32,612
My son...

309
00:12:32,612 --> 00:12:35,915
grew up in a loving, close-knit family,

310
00:12:35,915 --> 00:12:38,618
showered with his parents' love.

311
00:12:38,618 --> 00:12:40,720
We also have...

312
00:12:40,720 --> 00:12:42,956
a small home ready for him in Yongsan.

313
00:12:42,956 --> 00:12:45,692
He owns a home in Yongsan.

314
00:12:45,692 --> 00:12:47,393
That's incredible.

315
00:12:48,061 --> 00:12:48,895
That's a major selling point.

316
00:12:48,895 --> 00:12:51,431
We can't compete with that.
He owns a place in Yongsan.

317
00:12:52,165 --> 00:12:54,367
My son's ideal woman...

318
00:12:54,367 --> 00:12:55,668
is slender,

319
00:12:55,668 --> 00:12:59,272
pretty, and feminine.

320
00:13:00,607 --> 00:13:03,810
As for the daughter-in-law I hope for,

321
00:13:03,810 --> 00:13:05,612
I would like her to be Christian.

322
00:13:06,312 --> 00:13:08,514
- Religion came up.
- Here comes religion.

323
00:13:08,514 --> 00:13:12,118
If they get married,
I'll work very hard...

324
00:13:12,118 --> 00:13:15,588
to make sure she never feels burdened
by her in-laws.

325
00:13:15,588 --> 00:13:17,457
I truly mean that.

326
00:13:18,424 --> 00:13:19,759
You can feel her sincerity.

327
00:13:19,759 --> 00:13:23,062
And to avoid burdening my daughter-in-law,

328
00:13:23,062 --> 00:13:25,765
I don't plan to treat her
"like my own daughter."

329
00:13:26,366 --> 00:13:27,834
There's no such thing as
"a daughter-like daughter-in-law."

330
00:13:27,834 --> 00:13:30,603
Treating her like your own daughter...

331
00:13:30,603 --> 00:13:34,807
means trying to become
extremely close, right?

332
00:13:34,807 --> 00:13:38,278
And that can lead to conflict.

333
00:13:39,245 --> 00:13:41,514
And during the holidays,

334
00:13:41,514 --> 00:13:44,984
we'll travel or meet somewhere for a meal,

335
00:13:44,984 --> 00:13:48,021
chat for a while,
then go our separate ways.

336
00:13:48,021 --> 00:13:49,255
Goodness.

337
00:13:49,255 --> 00:13:52,325
She's saying all the good things.

338
00:13:52,325 --> 00:13:53,960
What a future mother-in-law.

339
00:13:55,662 --> 00:13:56,963
Isn't that wonderful?

340
00:13:58,865 --> 00:13:59,966
Thank you.

341
00:13:59,966 --> 00:14:02,368
(She ends with a sincere promise.)

342
00:14:04,137 --> 00:14:05,238
Yes?

343
00:14:05,238 --> 00:14:07,807
Even if she isn't Christian now,

344
00:14:09,475 --> 00:14:12,278
could she start attending church with you?

345
00:14:12,278 --> 00:14:13,880
Is she saying she'd convert?

346
00:14:13,880 --> 00:14:16,449
She's asking
whether they can work toward it.

347
00:14:16,916 --> 00:14:19,152
I'd love her to be Christian,

348
00:14:19,152 --> 00:14:23,156
but if she were someone
Ye Chan truly loved,

349
00:14:23,156 --> 00:14:25,291
I'd keep an open mind.

350
00:14:25,291 --> 00:14:29,062
After marriage,
both sets of parents will grow older...

351
00:14:29,062 --> 00:14:32,232
and may fall ill.
When major issues like that arise,

352
00:14:32,232 --> 00:14:35,101
I hope she shares my values...

353
00:14:35,101 --> 00:14:36,836
so we can talk things through together.

354
00:14:36,836 --> 00:14:41,040
That's one reason faith matters to me.

355
00:14:41,040 --> 00:14:42,876
Yes, shared values are important.

356
00:14:43,309 --> 00:14:44,777
Were you raised Christian?

357
00:14:44,777 --> 00:14:45,812
Yes, I was.

358
00:14:46,145 --> 00:14:48,414
How many generations of Christians
are in your family,

359
00:14:49,616 --> 00:14:51,885
- starting with your grandfather?
- I'm not exactly sure.

360
00:14:51,885 --> 00:14:54,354
Three generations.
He's the third generation.

361
00:14:54,354 --> 00:14:57,190
Christianity must be
very important to them.

362
00:14:57,190 --> 00:14:58,258
Exactly.

363
00:14:58,258 --> 00:15:00,159
It sounds like Christianity
is nonnegotiable.

364
00:15:00,159 --> 00:15:01,027
No, not at all.

365
00:15:01,027 --> 00:15:02,896
Not at all. It's just...

366
00:15:02,896 --> 00:15:05,465
If we had time for a deeper conversation,
I could explain more,

367
00:15:05,465 --> 00:15:08,234
but since I have to keep it brief...

368
00:15:08,234 --> 00:15:10,036
That's just how it sounded.

369
00:15:11,471 --> 00:15:13,439
Where are you currently working?

370
00:15:13,439 --> 00:15:15,975
At the Gwangju District
Prosecutors' Office.

371
00:15:15,975 --> 00:15:17,810
Gwangju in Jeolla Province.

372
00:15:17,810 --> 00:15:20,547
In about two months,
I'll finish my service,

373
00:15:20,547 --> 00:15:23,249
then move to Gangnam
to work at a law firm.

374
00:15:23,249 --> 00:15:25,118
His family home is in Seocho-gu, Gangnam.

375
00:15:25,118 --> 00:15:26,452
So he'll be moving back here.

376
00:15:26,452 --> 00:15:27,754
Yes, that's where my family lives.

377
00:15:28,788 --> 00:15:29,656
Yes?

378
00:15:29,656 --> 00:15:32,325
Your mother said your ideal woman...

379
00:15:32,325 --> 00:15:36,529
is slender and feminine,

380
00:15:36,529 --> 00:15:38,698
but could you be a little more specific?

381
00:15:38,698 --> 00:15:40,533
Do you mean more details about looks?

382
00:15:41,434 --> 00:15:45,071
I definitely prefer
someone with a glamorous look.

383
00:15:45,071 --> 00:15:46,773
I've been that way since kindergarten.

384
00:15:46,773 --> 00:15:48,575
(His tastes have been unwavering
since kindergarten.)

385
00:15:48,575 --> 00:15:50,143
That's probably your mother's influence.

386
00:15:50,143 --> 00:15:51,911
She's very glamorous and beautiful.

387
00:15:51,911 --> 00:15:53,513
I'm sure that has something to do with it.

388
00:15:53,513 --> 00:15:54,847
(Shy)

389
00:15:54,847 --> 00:15:57,584
When would you like to get married?

390
00:15:57,584 --> 00:16:00,053
The questions just keep coming.

391
00:16:00,053 --> 00:16:01,988
As I mentioned earlier,

392
00:16:01,988 --> 00:16:04,857
my service as a public-service lawyer
is nearly over,

393
00:16:04,857 --> 00:16:07,527
and I plan to settle in Seoul.

394
00:16:07,527 --> 00:16:10,530
From now on, I want to date seriously,

395
00:16:10,530 --> 00:16:12,565
with marriage in mind.

396
00:16:12,565 --> 00:16:15,969
As for marriage, I'm ready.

397
00:16:15,969 --> 00:16:18,538
I have all the finances in place,

398
00:16:18,538 --> 00:16:22,575
so even if he met someone and said,
"Mom, I want to marry her next month,"

399
00:16:22,575 --> 00:16:23,376
I would...

400
00:16:23,376 --> 00:16:24,644
That's how serious she is.

401
00:16:26,079 --> 00:16:28,715
So his future wife
could come empty-handed?

402
00:16:29,182 --> 00:16:32,652
She really could, if she's right for him.

403
00:16:32,652 --> 00:16:34,454
If she truly loves my son and...

404
00:16:35,188 --> 00:16:36,589
That's how you feel.

405
00:16:37,190 --> 00:16:38,157
Good place to stop.

406
00:16:41,194 --> 00:16:42,328
We'll conclude the introduction here.

407
00:16:42,328 --> 00:16:43,329
Thank you.

408
00:16:45,064 --> 00:16:46,432
Ye Chan is going to be popular.

409
00:16:47,166 --> 00:16:48,434
In my opinion,

410
00:16:48,434 --> 00:16:51,871
that introduction could win over...

411
00:16:51,871 --> 00:16:56,242
both the women and their mothers.

412
00:16:56,242 --> 00:16:58,578
She was so witty and did a wonderful job.

413
00:16:58,578 --> 00:17:00,747
- She seems to have charmed everyone.
- Exactly.

414
00:17:02,315 --> 00:17:05,218
(Kim Dong Young and his mother are third.)

415
00:17:05,218 --> 00:17:06,085
I'm curious.

416
00:17:06,085 --> 00:17:09,289
I'm dying to know what he does.

417
00:17:09,289 --> 00:17:12,992
Hello, I'm Choi Bok Hee,
Kim Dong Young's mother.

418
00:17:13,359 --> 00:17:16,095
My precious son, Dong Young,

419
00:17:16,095 --> 00:17:18,898
was born in 1993 and is now 34 years old.

420
00:17:21,968 --> 00:17:25,905
He works in pharmaceutical sales.

421
00:17:27,607 --> 00:17:29,475
Pharmaceutical sales.

422
00:17:30,343 --> 00:17:34,514
(Dong Young is a sales manager
at a pharmaceutical company.)

423
00:17:34,514 --> 00:17:36,583
He currently works in Busan,

424
00:17:36,583 --> 00:17:39,085
and he is so good at his job...

425
00:17:39,085 --> 00:17:42,055
that he even received an award
from the CEO.

426
00:17:45,058 --> 00:17:46,125
This is bad.

427
00:17:47,694 --> 00:17:50,663
He's diligent and hardworking,

428
00:17:50,663 --> 00:17:53,032
and saves over 70 percent of his salary.

429
00:17:53,032 --> 00:17:56,836
He also earns well. We live together now,

430
00:17:56,836 --> 00:18:00,807
but he can afford to move out anytime.

431
00:18:01,107 --> 00:18:02,175
Isn't that right, son?

432
00:18:03,610 --> 00:18:05,044
- She's adorable.
- She really is.

433
00:18:06,145 --> 00:18:07,547
Another one of his strengths is that...

434
00:18:07,547 --> 00:18:10,083
as you can see, he's 180 cm tall.

435
00:18:10,083 --> 00:18:13,519
He has worked out for years
and has a solid build.

436
00:18:13,519 --> 00:18:15,955
His daily routine is
as wholesome as it gets.

437
00:18:15,955 --> 00:18:20,360
Work, home, and the gym.

438
00:18:20,927 --> 00:18:23,296
So if you can't reach him for a while,

439
00:18:23,296 --> 00:18:26,466
he's probably lifting again.

440
00:18:26,966 --> 00:18:29,302
"Lifting" is a pretty technical term.

441
00:18:29,302 --> 00:18:30,470
Lifting.

442
00:18:30,470 --> 00:18:31,905
My son's ideal woman...

443
00:18:31,905 --> 00:18:35,642
has pretty eyes and an innocent look.

444
00:18:35,642 --> 00:18:38,578
Personality-wise,
he wants someone frugal like him...

445
00:18:38,578 --> 00:18:41,748
and devoted to her family.

446
00:18:41,748 --> 00:18:45,451
I sincerely hope
he meets a kindhearted woman...

447
00:18:45,451 --> 00:18:49,155
and builds something beautiful with her.

448
00:18:49,589 --> 00:18:52,191
Please give Dong Young a chance.

449
00:18:53,893 --> 00:18:55,428
She's so cute.

450
00:18:56,229 --> 00:18:57,864
So he lives in Busan?

451
00:18:58,665 --> 00:18:59,632
Did she say?

452
00:19:00,567 --> 00:19:03,536
Then where do you live now?

453
00:19:03,536 --> 00:19:05,471
I live in Gimhae.

454
00:19:05,471 --> 00:19:07,874
- Gimhae, South Gyeongsang Province.
- Gimhae.

455
00:19:08,541 --> 00:19:09,609
That's far.

456
00:19:10,443 --> 00:19:13,580
- Distance matters too.
- Yes, it does.

457
00:19:13,580 --> 00:19:16,549
That could be a bit of an issue...

458
00:19:16,549 --> 00:19:18,384
because he can't suddenly change jobs.

459
00:19:18,384 --> 00:19:19,552
Right.

460
00:19:19,552 --> 00:19:22,088
We live together now, but naturally,

461
00:19:22,355 --> 00:19:25,325
if he moved closer to the woman,
he'd get his own place.

462
00:19:25,325 --> 00:19:28,761
I think he'd go wherever she is.

463
00:19:30,897 --> 00:19:32,098
No questions?

464
00:19:32,098 --> 00:19:33,833
The previous introduction
set the bar too high.

465
00:19:35,401 --> 00:19:37,437
- Please ask us lots of questions.
- My goodness.

466
00:19:38,404 --> 00:19:42,008
What do you think
of long-distance relationships?

467
00:19:42,008 --> 00:19:45,278
If you've had one before,

468
00:19:45,278 --> 00:19:48,314
how long did it last?

469
00:19:51,517 --> 00:19:54,254
As long as the woman and her mother
are okay with it,

470
00:19:54,254 --> 00:19:56,256
I'll go anywhere...

471
00:19:56,956 --> 00:19:58,992
south of the 38th parallel...

472
00:19:59,726 --> 00:20:01,628
anytime.

473
00:20:01,628 --> 00:20:02,695
That was clever.

474
00:20:03,129 --> 00:20:06,399
Exactly. He needs that kind of resolve.

475
00:20:07,500 --> 00:20:08,635
The 38th parallel.

476
00:20:10,703 --> 00:20:11,905
Well...

477
00:20:11,905 --> 00:20:14,274
Ha Yoon just sighed.

478
00:20:14,274 --> 00:20:17,176
I've done long distance before,

479
00:20:17,176 --> 00:20:20,613
and honestly, feelings matter more...

480
00:20:21,047 --> 00:20:23,149
than time or distance.

481
00:20:23,149 --> 00:20:25,051
If I meet a woman I like,

482
00:20:25,051 --> 00:20:27,520
I'll go anywhere
south of the 38th parallel.

483
00:20:30,490 --> 00:20:32,025
Here's what I'm curious about.

484
00:20:32,025 --> 00:20:36,229
You seem firmly established in Gimhae.

485
00:20:36,229 --> 00:20:40,366
If you moved to Seoul
to be closer to your partner,

486
00:20:40,366 --> 00:20:44,237
you'd have to start over.

487
00:20:44,237 --> 00:20:47,240
Would you be willing to do that?

488
00:20:48,007 --> 00:20:50,843
That's true,
because he has his client base there.

489
00:20:50,843 --> 00:20:52,045
I didn't think of that.

490
00:20:53,813 --> 00:20:55,481
I currently live in Gimhae,

491
00:20:56,482 --> 00:20:57,717
and I work in Busan.

492
00:20:57,717 --> 00:20:59,919
Even establishing myself in Busan...

493
00:20:59,919 --> 00:21:01,788
- Couldn't have been easy.
- It was, actually.

494
00:21:01,788 --> 00:21:03,389
It wasn't difficult.

495
00:21:03,389 --> 00:21:04,824
It was actually quite easy.

496
00:21:04,824 --> 00:21:05,825
So you're good at what you do.

497
00:21:05,825 --> 00:21:08,061
- It's my calling.
- Good.

498
00:21:08,061 --> 00:21:10,396
You're confident you can work anywhere.

499
00:21:10,396 --> 00:21:11,264
Anywhere.

500
00:21:11,264 --> 00:21:15,068
My job is about meeting people,

501
00:21:15,068 --> 00:21:17,036
so whether they're in Seoul...

502
00:21:17,036 --> 00:21:19,205
or even North Hamgyong Province,
it doesn't matter.

503
00:21:19,205 --> 00:21:20,073
North Hamgyong Province.

504
00:21:21,374 --> 00:21:22,242
Thank you.

505
00:21:27,347 --> 00:21:31,317
I'm worried about
what the mothers will think.

506
00:21:31,317 --> 00:21:33,119
First, there's the distance.

507
00:21:33,119 --> 00:21:37,390
Ha Yoon looks a little disappointed too.
It's so far, that's why.

508
00:21:37,390 --> 00:21:39,359
Right. They had a connection before.

509
00:21:39,359 --> 00:21:40,293
Exactly.

510
00:21:42,462 --> 00:21:44,330
(Kang Shin Woo and his mother
are up fourth.)

511
00:21:44,330 --> 00:21:45,365
Hello.

512
00:21:47,634 --> 00:21:49,335
- The man who goes all in.
- Now, Kang Shin Woo.

513
00:21:49,702 --> 00:21:52,272
I'm Park Gyeong Ja,
Kang Shin Woo's mother.

514
00:21:53,172 --> 00:21:59,178
My son was born in 1992
and is 35 this year.

515
00:21:59,946 --> 00:22:03,416
And my son is...

516
00:22:05,485 --> 00:22:06,553
a doctor of Korean medicine.

517
00:22:09,622 --> 00:22:10,657
A doctor of Korean medicine.

518
00:22:12,425 --> 00:22:13,526
I knew it.

519
00:22:13,526 --> 00:22:15,195
Ha Yoon is one too.

520
00:22:15,195 --> 00:22:16,362
That's right.

521
00:22:18,298 --> 00:22:20,567
He currently runs...

522
00:22:20,567 --> 00:22:22,835
his own Korean medicine
rehabilitation clinic...

523
00:22:22,835 --> 00:22:26,172
near SNUE Station,
which he opened himself.

524
00:22:27,473 --> 00:22:29,108
Now that I look at him,

525
00:22:29,108 --> 00:22:31,411
- He looks the part.
- he does look the part.

526
00:22:31,411 --> 00:22:35,548
He really looks like
a doctor of Korean medicine.

527
00:22:36,382 --> 00:22:40,520
He studied Korean medicine
at Dongguk University...

528
00:22:40,520 --> 00:22:43,590
on scholarships for all six years.

529
00:22:43,590 --> 00:22:46,159
He continued his studies...

530
00:22:46,159 --> 00:22:50,363
and earned a doctorate
in Korean medicine there.

531
00:22:50,363 --> 00:22:53,600
He is so highly regarded...

532
00:22:53,600 --> 00:22:56,870
that he was even offered
a university hospital faculty position.

533
00:22:58,271 --> 00:23:02,775
And if the family sleeps in
on a weekend morning,

534
00:23:02,775 --> 00:23:04,677
he orders groceries
for early-morning delivery...

535
00:23:04,677 --> 00:23:08,147
and cooks for us. He's very caring.

536
00:23:09,782 --> 00:23:11,017
That's sweet.

537
00:23:11,384 --> 00:23:13,419
I had a feeling he'd be very caring.

538
00:23:13,419 --> 00:23:15,855
So to me, he truly is...

539
00:23:15,855 --> 00:23:18,791
a dependable source of strength.

540
00:23:20,693 --> 00:23:22,262
My son's ideal woman...

541
00:23:22,929 --> 00:23:27,500
knows how to dress well
and has striking, fox-like features.

542
00:23:27,901 --> 00:23:29,402
That's Da Hye.

543
00:23:29,869 --> 00:23:31,471
Since he recently opened his clinic...

544
00:23:31,471 --> 00:23:34,774
and will be busy for the next five years,

545
00:23:34,774 --> 00:23:38,177
I'd prefer someone with a stable career.

546
00:23:40,547 --> 00:23:41,781
Finally...

547
00:23:41,781 --> 00:23:42,749
(Sigh)

548
00:23:43,383 --> 00:23:45,685
My son also has Ari,

549
00:23:45,685 --> 00:23:50,223
a 35-kg golden retriever.

550
00:23:50,223 --> 00:23:52,659
I hope she will treat Ari like family...

551
00:23:52,659 --> 00:23:53,526
Thirty-five kilograms?

552
00:23:53,526 --> 00:23:55,428
and have a warm enough heart...

553
00:23:55,428 --> 00:23:58,865
to love Ari too.

554
00:23:58,865 --> 00:24:02,235
That's my greatest wish.

555
00:24:02,235 --> 00:24:04,037
That could be...

556
00:24:05,071 --> 00:24:07,373
a bit of an issue.

557
00:24:07,373 --> 00:24:09,576
A 35-kg retriever...

558
00:24:09,576 --> 00:24:10,610
is enormous.

559
00:24:10,610 --> 00:24:11,945
It's really big.

560
00:24:11,945 --> 00:24:14,847
For someone who's never had a dog,
the shedding...

561
00:24:14,847 --> 00:24:15,715
Right.

562
00:24:15,715 --> 00:24:19,919
and so many other things
open up a whole new world.

563
00:24:19,919 --> 00:24:22,622
Whether they can handle all of that...

564
00:24:22,622 --> 00:24:24,257
is going to matter a lot.

565
00:24:24,257 --> 00:24:25,825
He should meet another dog lover.

566
00:24:25,825 --> 00:24:28,361
Right. He needs someone who likes dogs.

567
00:24:28,361 --> 00:24:29,329
Right.

568
00:24:29,929 --> 00:24:31,998
Where do you currently live?

569
00:24:31,998 --> 00:24:36,002
I've lived in Gwacheon
for more than ten years.

570
00:24:36,002 --> 00:24:37,670
I'm always in poor health,

571
00:24:37,670 --> 00:24:40,273
so I was hoping to visit
if your clinic was nearby.

572
00:24:41,007 --> 00:24:44,911
But there's another doctor of
Korean medicine right beside her.

573
00:24:44,911 --> 00:24:48,047
Why would she go
all the way to his clinic?

574
00:24:48,047 --> 00:24:50,850
Ma'am, my clinic is near SNUE Station
in Gangnam.

575
00:24:52,085 --> 00:24:53,386
Goodness, that's so close.

576
00:24:53,386 --> 00:24:54,821
Very close.

577
00:24:56,289 --> 00:24:58,057
Earlier, your mother said...

578
00:24:58,057 --> 00:25:01,928
she hopes the woman has a stable career.

579
00:25:01,928 --> 00:25:03,530
Do you feel the same way, Shin Woo?

580
00:25:03,530 --> 00:25:06,799
I feel the opposite.
Stability isn't a must.

581
00:25:06,799 --> 00:25:10,503
I'd prefer someone
who strives to improve herself...

582
00:25:10,503 --> 00:25:12,405
and keeps growing and evolving.

583
00:25:12,405 --> 00:25:13,473
Someone who keeps evolving.

584
00:25:14,807 --> 00:25:17,243
When do you plan to get married?

585
00:25:17,243 --> 00:25:18,444
As for my marriage,

586
00:25:18,444 --> 00:25:20,580
I would like us to get to know each other
through all four seasons,

587
00:25:20,580 --> 00:25:22,115
and once we are sure about marriage,

588
00:25:22,115 --> 00:25:23,950
we would prepare for about a year
and then marry.

589
00:25:23,950 --> 00:25:25,952
That fits my life plan.

590
00:25:25,952 --> 00:25:27,320
One more question.

591
00:25:27,320 --> 00:25:29,389
You and your partner
could have different faiths, right?

592
00:25:29,389 --> 00:25:31,157
I'm sorry, but what religion are you?

593
00:25:31,157 --> 00:25:33,059
- I'm not religious.
- No religion?

594
00:25:33,059 --> 00:25:35,361
If you fell for someone,

595
00:25:35,361 --> 00:25:37,664
would you be willing
to convert to her religion?

596
00:25:37,664 --> 00:25:41,367
Faith is deeply personal,

597
00:25:41,367 --> 00:25:44,704
so I can't promise...

598
00:25:44,704 --> 00:25:46,506
that I would be moved to believe,

599
00:25:46,506 --> 00:25:48,775
but I'd be willing to try.

600
00:25:48,775 --> 00:25:50,343
By any chance,

601
00:25:50,343 --> 00:25:53,479
are you always willing to volunteer too?

602
00:25:53,479 --> 00:25:55,848
Da Hye's mother...

603
00:25:55,848 --> 00:25:58,451
- She's really going for it.
- just asked...

604
00:25:58,751 --> 00:26:01,788
five questions in a row.

605
00:26:01,788 --> 00:26:04,257
This is turning into a job interview.

606
00:26:04,958 --> 00:26:07,493
People ask why I volunteer so much.

607
00:26:07,493 --> 00:26:09,162
That's how often I do it.

608
00:26:09,162 --> 00:26:10,797
Even if I have to make the time,

609
00:26:10,797 --> 00:26:12,932
I volunteer whenever I can.

610
00:26:12,932 --> 00:26:13,933
Volunteering.

611
00:26:14,767 --> 00:26:17,070
The questions are much tougher
than yesterday.

612
00:26:18,304 --> 00:26:20,206
Marrying off a daughter isn't easy.

613
00:26:22,242 --> 00:26:23,977
It's an in-depth interview, right?

614
00:26:23,977 --> 00:26:26,212
A stress interview.

615
00:26:28,915 --> 00:26:32,085
How many women
do you currently have your eye on?

616
00:26:33,019 --> 00:26:34,354
(Chuckling)

617
00:26:36,089 --> 00:26:37,223
Why is he so happy?

618
00:26:38,324 --> 00:26:39,692
He's adorable.

619
00:26:41,060 --> 00:26:42,395
Right now, one.

620
00:26:44,464 --> 00:26:45,965
He only has eyes for one.

621
00:26:45,965 --> 00:26:46,933
But his mother...

622
00:26:46,933 --> 00:26:48,868
His mother doesn't like that.

623
00:26:48,868 --> 00:26:51,204
His mother doesn't like it.
She's frustrated.

624
00:26:54,240 --> 00:26:56,175
I think it shows.

625
00:26:56,175 --> 00:26:57,377
As of now.

626
00:26:57,377 --> 00:26:59,712
- I haven't mentioned who it is.
- It's only Day Three.

627
00:27:00,346 --> 00:27:03,349
- I have about three in mind.
- Three.

628
00:27:03,349 --> 00:27:04,851
I think what she's saying is,

629
00:27:04,851 --> 00:27:08,621
"It's not like you're lacking anything."

630
00:27:08,621 --> 00:27:09,756
"So why go all in?"

631
00:27:09,756 --> 00:27:13,159
"Why only see this one woman?"
That's what I think she means.

632
00:27:13,159 --> 00:27:14,327
That's understandable.

633
00:27:14,327 --> 00:27:15,562
But her son...

634
00:27:15,562 --> 00:27:17,797
He was smitten at first sight.

635
00:27:17,797 --> 00:27:21,167
From Da Hye's perspective,
he made it far too obvious.

636
00:27:21,167 --> 00:27:24,604
It could feel a little overwhelming.

637
00:27:24,604 --> 00:27:27,273
And with his mother putting on the brakes,

638
00:27:27,273 --> 00:27:29,976
it must be confusing too.

639
00:27:31,177 --> 00:27:32,378
- Hello.
- Hello.

640
00:27:32,378 --> 00:27:34,480
I'm curious about Seong Mo too.

641
00:27:35,615 --> 00:27:38,585
I'm Kim Yong Mi, Moon Seong Mo's mother.

642
00:27:38,585 --> 00:27:40,153
My son, Seong Mo,

643
00:27:40,153 --> 00:27:44,524
was born in December 1992 and is 35.

644
00:27:45,225 --> 00:27:46,726
They're all so much older than I am.

645
00:27:47,760 --> 00:27:49,162
I'm the oldest one here.

646
00:27:49,796 --> 00:27:52,532
He's a professional golfer.

647
00:27:53,633 --> 00:27:55,235
There was one on the show last season too.

648
00:27:59,772 --> 00:28:02,475
He now works as a freelancer.

649
00:28:02,475 --> 00:28:03,743
At present,

650
00:28:03,743 --> 00:28:08,681
he is carving out his own path
in many fields,

651
00:28:08,681 --> 00:28:12,085
including golf lessons, ads,
events, and modeling.

652
00:28:13,953 --> 00:28:15,588
He's an athlete.

653
00:28:17,590 --> 00:28:20,827
First, my son is 183 cm tall.

654
00:28:20,827 --> 00:28:21,728
He's tall and handsome.

655
00:28:21,728 --> 00:28:25,398
As you'd expect from an athlete,

656
00:28:25,398 --> 00:28:26,866
he has a strong build
and excellent stamina.

657
00:28:26,866 --> 00:28:29,435
So no matter whom he meets,

658
00:28:29,435 --> 00:28:32,438
I know he'll make her feel
safe and protected.

659
00:28:35,375 --> 00:28:37,944
He currently lives in Gangnam, Seoul.

660
00:28:37,944 --> 00:28:40,713
He is working steadily...

661
00:28:40,713 --> 00:28:42,415
toward buying a home of his own.

662
00:28:43,416 --> 00:28:45,218
He isn't a big spender,

663
00:28:45,218 --> 00:28:47,987
so he lives quite comfortably.

664
00:28:47,987 --> 00:28:52,992
But he never hesitates to spend on family.

665
00:28:53,660 --> 00:28:57,263
He drove a used car for many years,

666
00:28:58,331 --> 00:29:02,001
yet bought me an electric car.

667
00:29:02,001 --> 00:29:04,170
When it matters, he knows...

668
00:29:04,170 --> 00:29:06,773
how to express his love wholeheartedly.

669
00:29:06,773 --> 00:29:08,007
He's exactly like me.

670
00:29:08,641 --> 00:29:10,076
My son's ideal woman...

671
00:29:10,076 --> 00:29:12,912
is cute and honest,

672
00:29:12,912 --> 00:29:16,749
polite to elders, and humble.

673
00:29:16,749 --> 00:29:19,686
I hope he finds a good partner
who respects him,

674
00:29:19,686 --> 00:29:24,958
and they build a relationship
based on shared responsibility.

675
00:29:24,958 --> 00:29:25,892
Thank you.

676
00:29:29,262 --> 00:29:32,565
What hobbies do you have besides golf?

677
00:29:32,565 --> 00:29:35,635
I enjoy doing CrossFit.

678
00:29:35,902 --> 00:29:37,570
It helps me relieve stress.

679
00:29:37,570 --> 00:29:40,907
Does your partner
need to work out with you?

680
00:29:41,841 --> 00:29:44,644
No. I get that question a lot.

681
00:29:44,644 --> 00:29:46,079
It'd be nice if she exercised,

682
00:29:46,079 --> 00:29:49,282
but I'd just like her
to respect my workout time.

683
00:29:50,283 --> 00:29:51,351
She doesn't have to join me.

684
00:29:52,819 --> 00:29:55,889
Do you prefer a partner...

685
00:29:55,889 --> 00:29:58,391
who's more energetic
and outgoing than you,

686
00:29:58,391 --> 00:30:02,562
or someone more like you
who's introverted?

687
00:30:02,562 --> 00:30:04,397
That's important.

688
00:30:04,397 --> 00:30:05,665
It is important.

689
00:30:05,665 --> 00:30:09,369
Someone too outgoing drains me.

690
00:30:09,369 --> 00:30:11,638
So I'd prefer someone similar to me,

691
00:30:11,638 --> 00:30:14,440
or at least not too energetic.

692
00:30:15,208 --> 00:30:17,310
How many women have caught your interest?

693
00:30:18,011 --> 00:30:20,280
I think three.

694
00:30:21,714 --> 00:30:23,016
That's a lot.

695
00:30:23,016 --> 00:30:24,150
I'm interested in all of them.

696
00:30:26,486 --> 00:30:27,387
Thank you.

697
00:30:29,088 --> 00:30:31,691
(The men's introductions end.)

698
00:30:32,158 --> 00:30:33,459
This is tough.

699
00:30:34,194 --> 00:30:35,828
They all have such impressive credentials.

700
00:30:35,828 --> 00:30:37,597
They were all really great.

701
00:30:37,597 --> 00:30:41,067
Their credentials were
even better than I expected.

702
00:30:41,768 --> 00:30:45,171
I thought, "A few men
are going to get all the votes."

703
00:30:46,706 --> 00:30:48,775
We've heard the men's introductions.

704
00:30:48,775 --> 00:30:51,244
Who do you think will be the most popular?

705
00:30:51,244 --> 00:30:52,946
The licensed professionals.

706
00:30:52,946 --> 00:30:55,248
The lawyer
and the doctor of Korean medicine.

707
00:30:55,248 --> 00:30:57,784
That's right.
They were flooded with questions.

708
00:30:57,784 --> 00:31:01,688
On top of that, Ye Chan's...

709
00:31:01,688 --> 00:31:04,424
mother gave a great presentation.

710
00:31:04,424 --> 00:31:06,059
That's right. She really did.

711
00:31:06,059 --> 00:31:07,994
And he already has a home.

712
00:31:07,994 --> 00:31:09,128
He owns a place in Yongsan.

713
00:31:09,128 --> 00:31:10,096
And...

714
00:31:10,096 --> 00:31:11,998
surprisingly, though,

715
00:31:11,998 --> 00:31:14,334
announcer Lee In Kwon...

716
00:31:14,334 --> 00:31:15,435
may be popular too.

717
00:31:15,435 --> 00:31:18,204
Yes, I think the mothers will like him.

718
00:31:18,204 --> 00:31:20,840
I think he could be a strong contender.

719
00:31:21,207 --> 00:31:24,777
The women's mothers
will choose the dates today.

720
00:31:28,882 --> 00:31:32,585
Each mother will choose
the man she wants her daughter to date...

721
00:31:32,585 --> 00:31:34,320
and stand beside him.

722
00:31:36,089 --> 00:31:40,460
Today's dates will be decided
solely by the mothers.

723
00:31:40,460 --> 00:31:44,264
As before, mothers and daughters
cannot consult each other.

724
00:31:46,866 --> 00:31:48,268
I think the mothers...

725
00:31:48,268 --> 00:31:52,005
will gravitate toward
licensed professionals.

726
00:31:52,005 --> 00:31:54,908
I expect about two votes.

727
00:31:54,908 --> 00:31:57,810
- As an eligible bachelor,
- He sounds very confident.

728
00:31:57,810 --> 00:31:59,245
I don't think
I have any major shortcomings.

729
00:31:59,245 --> 00:32:01,981
That's what led me to that estimate.

730
00:32:02,715 --> 00:32:04,350
I expect zero votes.

731
00:32:04,350 --> 00:32:06,019
There are quite a few Christians here.

732
00:32:06,019 --> 00:32:08,087
Since I don't have a religion yet,

733
00:32:08,087 --> 00:32:11,958
they may prefer men who share their faith.

734
00:32:11,958 --> 00:32:14,294
That's made me less confident.

735
00:32:15,361 --> 00:32:18,264
(What will the women's mothers choose?)

736
00:32:19,432 --> 00:32:20,900
- I'm getting nervous too.
- You are, right?

737
00:32:21,434 --> 00:32:22,168
Do Yoon.

738
00:32:22,168 --> 00:32:24,003
The Samsung Electronics employee.

739
00:32:24,003 --> 00:32:26,339
Personally, I hope she chooses In Kwon.

740
00:32:29,042 --> 00:32:31,511
I'm hoping for one vote.

741
00:32:32,178 --> 00:32:36,683
Do Yoon seemed a little interested in me.

742
00:32:37,217 --> 00:32:40,787
The introductions changed my feelings.

743
00:32:40,787 --> 00:32:43,456
In Kwon is nine years older than me.

744
00:32:43,456 --> 00:32:44,557
Is that a little much?

745
00:32:44,557 --> 00:32:47,193
Ye Chan is six years older too,

746
00:32:47,193 --> 00:32:50,763
but nine years feels like a huge gap.
That's holding me back.

747
00:32:50,763 --> 00:32:52,232
Nine years.

748
00:32:52,432 --> 00:32:55,902
Ahn Do Yoon is 28,
the only one here in her twenties.

749
00:32:55,902 --> 00:32:59,372
When you're in your twenties,
nine years feels like a huge gap.

750
00:32:59,372 --> 00:33:00,340
Right.

751
00:33:00,340 --> 00:33:02,108
But the mothers are choosing this time.

752
00:33:02,108 --> 00:33:04,844
So the daughters have no idea.

753
00:33:04,844 --> 00:33:05,612
That's right.

754
00:33:07,313 --> 00:33:09,749
He has a stable career,

755
00:33:09,749 --> 00:33:12,619
and he seems like a great fit
for our family.

756
00:33:12,619 --> 00:33:14,320
That made the choice fairly easy.

757
00:33:20,527 --> 00:33:21,794
Lee In Kwon.

758
00:33:21,794 --> 00:33:24,230
(She passes Lee In Kwon.)

759
00:33:25,865 --> 00:33:29,969
(She walks straight past
Lee In Kwon and...)

760
00:33:31,304 --> 00:33:32,872
(Swerve)

761
00:33:32,872 --> 00:33:34,407
Stand in front of me, right here.

762
00:33:34,941 --> 00:33:37,310
Of course, exactly as expected.

763
00:33:37,310 --> 00:33:38,111
That's right.

764
00:33:38,111 --> 00:33:40,747
- Hello.
- Thank you.

765
00:33:40,747 --> 00:33:41,781
(Ahn Do Yoon's mother
chooses Kwon Ye Chan.)

766
00:33:43,049 --> 00:33:44,350
- We meet again.
- Yes, we do.

767
00:33:44,350 --> 00:33:45,351
Hello.

768
00:33:46,853 --> 00:33:47,720
Thank you.

769
00:33:48,154 --> 00:33:49,656
Thank you.

770
00:33:50,924 --> 00:33:52,191
Thank you.

771
00:33:52,825 --> 00:33:54,427
Thank you, Ms. Son.

772
00:33:55,862 --> 00:33:57,363
Now you know how I felt yesterday, right?

773
00:33:58,865 --> 00:34:00,867
- This makes you extremely nervous.
- Of course.

774
00:34:00,867 --> 00:34:03,937
I heard he liked Do Yoon more
after the date yesterday.

775
00:34:03,937 --> 00:34:04,804
That's a relief.

776
00:34:05,138 --> 00:34:07,140
Ye Chan is so popular.

777
00:34:07,140 --> 00:34:08,841
No, not at all.

778
00:34:11,288 --> 00:34:12,812
You're nervous, aren't you?

779
00:34:12,812 --> 00:34:14,847
That sound makes me nervous.

780
00:34:14,847 --> 00:34:15,815
It does.

781
00:34:15,815 --> 00:34:17,016
That creak.

782
00:34:17,016 --> 00:34:18,384
I think everyone would be
more nervous than yesterday.

783
00:34:18,384 --> 00:34:19,185
Yes.

784
00:34:25,191 --> 00:34:26,826
(Second to go, Kim Da Hye's mother)

785
00:34:26,826 --> 00:34:28,528
Now, let's see.

786
00:34:28,528 --> 00:34:30,396
As for Da Hye...

787
00:34:38,238 --> 00:34:41,407
The person I most want to date...

788
00:34:41,407 --> 00:34:43,676
is Ye Chan.

789
00:34:43,676 --> 00:34:45,778
- She changed her mind.
- Because...

790
00:34:45,778 --> 00:34:50,850
how his mother described Ye Chan...

791
00:34:50,850 --> 00:34:54,053
and the future she envisions
for his family...

792
00:34:54,053 --> 00:34:59,092
are so similar to
what I've always envisioned for myself.

793
00:34:59,092 --> 00:35:02,762
It made me want to
talk with him once more.

794
00:35:03,096 --> 00:35:04,631
They share the same faith too.

795
00:35:04,631 --> 00:35:05,498
That's true.

796
00:35:06,399 --> 00:35:09,669
She's already been
on three or four dates with Shin Woo.

797
00:35:09,669 --> 00:35:12,071
Ye Chan is a man of faith,

798
00:35:12,071 --> 00:35:14,107
and faith matters a lot to me.

799
00:35:14,107 --> 00:35:16,075
So I was very torn.

800
00:35:18,044 --> 00:35:19,979
She was torn,

801
00:35:19,979 --> 00:35:21,481
but when she learned Shin Woo was
a doctor of Korean medicine,

802
00:35:21,481 --> 00:35:25,084
she showed a lot of interest earlier.

803
00:35:26,352 --> 00:35:31,524
(Whom will Kim Da Hye's mother choose?)

804
00:35:35,228 --> 00:35:36,196
She walks right past him.

805
00:35:36,196 --> 00:35:39,065
(She passes her daughter's choice,
Kwon Ye Chan.)

806
00:35:41,601 --> 00:35:42,702
Should I go back?

807
00:35:42,702 --> 00:35:44,003
(U-turn)

808
00:35:44,704 --> 00:35:46,973
(Kim Da Hye's mother
changes direction again.)

809
00:35:46,973 --> 00:35:50,476
- Is she joining the crowd again?
- It's happening again.

810
00:35:53,479 --> 00:35:55,181
- No, we need to go this way.
- What?

811
00:35:55,882 --> 00:35:57,584
Where is she going?

812
00:35:58,551 --> 00:35:59,485
Seriously.

813
00:35:59,485 --> 00:36:01,087
(On the verge of tears)

814
00:36:01,621 --> 00:36:04,824
(She fools everyone and races ahead.)

815
00:36:05,892 --> 00:36:06,893
(Is it here?)

816
00:36:06,893 --> 00:36:07,961
(Nope)

817
00:36:08,661 --> 00:36:11,030
(Another victim falls for it.)

818
00:36:14,367 --> 00:36:15,335
I knew it.

819
00:36:15,335 --> 00:36:17,670
- Ma'am, I love you.
- I knew she'd choose him.

820
00:36:18,938 --> 00:36:22,775
At this point,
she's telling them to get married.

821
00:36:23,409 --> 00:36:27,447
She knows how much
Shin Woo likes her daughter.

822
00:36:27,447 --> 00:36:29,015
So she's given them her blessing.

823
00:36:29,015 --> 00:36:31,084
"Just marry
the doctor of Korean medicine."

824
00:36:31,084 --> 00:36:32,785
If you ask me, I think that's all it was.

825
00:36:36,222 --> 00:36:39,759
Da Hye doesn't look too pleased.

826
00:36:42,095 --> 00:36:44,497
(Welcome)

827
00:36:44,497 --> 00:36:45,532
Congratulations.

828
00:36:45,532 --> 00:36:47,400
- Thank you.
- Congratulations.

829
00:36:48,301 --> 00:36:49,903
The professional title won you over.

830
00:36:49,903 --> 00:36:51,170
It can't be helped.

831
00:36:51,170 --> 00:36:52,071
Did I fall for the credentials?

832
00:36:52,071 --> 00:36:53,540
He needs to take
his future mother-in-law's pulse.

833
00:36:54,974 --> 00:36:57,944
From the start,
Shin Woo came across as very likable.

834
00:36:57,944 --> 00:37:01,381
Then I learned his profession,
and when he mentioned volunteering,

835
00:37:01,381 --> 00:37:03,550
that really moved me.

836
00:37:05,552 --> 00:37:07,086
I feel on top of the world.

837
00:37:10,189 --> 00:37:13,226
You agreed to talk to everyone.

838
00:37:13,226 --> 00:37:14,394
I don't need to.

839
00:37:14,394 --> 00:37:15,929
My goodness.

840
00:37:16,563 --> 00:37:19,032
(Will the date chosen by her mother
change Da Hye's feelings?)

841
00:37:19,032 --> 00:37:20,800
Maybe just exchanging names
will be enough.

842
00:37:25,038 --> 00:37:26,206
(Third to go, Yang Ha Yoon's mother)

843
00:37:26,206 --> 00:37:28,107
The doctor of Korean medicine.

844
00:37:28,107 --> 00:37:29,475
Yes, Ha Yoon.

845
00:37:32,679 --> 00:37:35,848
(Three men still have no one beside them.)

846
00:37:36,282 --> 00:37:39,852
(Who will Yang Ha Yoon's mother choose?)

847
00:37:39,852 --> 00:37:41,821
More than anyone,

848
00:37:41,821 --> 00:37:45,124
I hope Ha Yoon comes to me.

849
00:37:45,124 --> 00:37:49,329
After yesterday's date
and even today's introductions,

850
00:37:49,329 --> 00:37:52,031
her saying she wanted to know me better...

851
00:37:52,599 --> 00:37:56,202
I'm really curious
to hear your introduction.

852
00:37:56,202 --> 00:37:58,338
Let's talk again after that.

853
00:37:59,839 --> 00:38:03,042
That stuck with me,
so that's where I stand.

854
00:38:03,610 --> 00:38:05,945
Ha Yoon and Dong Young had
such great chemistry before.

855
00:38:05,945 --> 00:38:07,013
That's right.

856
00:38:07,013 --> 00:38:09,849
But he's so far away, right?

857
00:38:10,416 --> 00:38:15,288
(Dong Young waits for Ha Yoon.)

858
00:38:15,655 --> 00:38:18,157
(Whom will Yang Ha Yoon's mother choose?)

859
00:38:19,959 --> 00:38:22,662
(She passes Lee In Kwon.)

860
00:38:22,929 --> 00:38:24,364
(Hesitating)

861
00:38:24,831 --> 00:38:28,868
(Ha Yoon's mother
changes direction midway.)

862
00:38:29,168 --> 00:38:32,105
(Ye Chan or Dong Young?)

863
00:38:37,377 --> 00:38:38,211
Thank you, ma'am.

864
00:38:38,211 --> 00:38:39,212
Of course.

865
00:38:39,712 --> 00:38:41,114
It can't be helped.

866
00:38:41,114 --> 00:38:41,948
Of course.

867
00:38:43,383 --> 00:38:45,885
Is any career going to beat "lawyer?"

868
00:38:46,319 --> 00:38:47,754
I'm a little jealous myself.

869
00:38:47,754 --> 00:38:49,789
See? This is why you study hard.

870
00:38:50,690 --> 00:38:51,691
Thank you, ma'am.

871
00:38:51,691 --> 00:38:55,361
(Lawyer Kwon Ye Chan receives 2 votes.)

872
00:39:01,000 --> 00:39:03,169
Thank you. Should she stand over there?

873
00:39:03,169 --> 00:39:04,270
- One on each side.
- Like this?

874
00:39:04,270 --> 00:39:05,838
Yes, like that.

875
00:39:05,838 --> 00:39:07,740
Thank you. My goodness.

876
00:39:10,043 --> 00:39:10,977
My goodness.

877
00:39:11,678 --> 00:39:15,848
I was hoping Ha Yoon would choose him.

878
00:39:15,848 --> 00:39:20,653
Dong Young seems very interested
in Ha Yoon so far.

879
00:39:20,653 --> 00:39:23,756
But now,
his chances of getting to know her...

880
00:39:23,756 --> 00:39:26,793
have dropped dramatically.

881
00:39:26,793 --> 00:39:27,760
That's sad.

882
00:39:28,862 --> 00:39:29,963
I'll do my best.

883
00:39:30,697 --> 00:39:32,599
Your mother won't be lonely.

884
00:39:37,170 --> 00:39:41,474
He said he'd go anywhere
south of the 38th parallel,

885
00:39:41,474 --> 00:39:44,611
but that's easier said than done.

886
00:39:44,611 --> 00:39:45,845
Absolutely.

887
00:39:45,845 --> 00:39:49,115
But Ye Chan lives nearby,

888
00:39:49,115 --> 00:39:53,286
and his mother said everything is ready
for his marriage.

889
00:39:53,286 --> 00:39:57,757
He's a professional,
and his other qualities are excellent too.

890
00:39:59,559 --> 00:40:00,894
My first choice...

891
00:40:00,894 --> 00:40:03,897
changed from Dong Young to Ye Chan.

892
00:40:04,731 --> 00:40:06,199
So it had already changed.

893
00:40:07,133 --> 00:40:08,868
Gimhae is too far.

894
00:40:08,868 --> 00:40:10,503
And...

895
00:40:10,503 --> 00:40:12,605
I don't want someone...

896
00:40:12,605 --> 00:40:15,675
to change his circumstances
or personality too much for me.

897
00:40:15,675 --> 00:40:18,011
That's why...

898
00:40:18,011 --> 00:40:21,080
And I don't want
another relationship to end.

899
00:40:22,782 --> 00:40:23,683
My heart...

900
00:40:24,817 --> 00:40:25,652
I'm sorry.

901
00:40:28,555 --> 00:40:29,489
I...

902
00:40:31,190 --> 00:40:33,526
want my next relationship
to lead to marriage.

903
00:40:33,526 --> 00:40:34,561
I'm sorry.

904
00:40:38,965 --> 00:40:41,401
I really didn't want to cry.

905
00:40:43,102 --> 00:40:44,237
Why is she crying?

906
00:40:44,604 --> 00:40:45,505
(Her tangled emotions
spill over into tears.)

907
00:40:45,505 --> 00:40:46,839
She's soft-hearted.

908
00:40:49,108 --> 00:40:52,378
Realistically, the person...

909
00:40:52,378 --> 00:40:55,882
I could get to know
without any major obstacles...

910
00:40:55,882 --> 00:40:59,018
seems to be Ye Chan.

911
00:41:00,553 --> 00:41:05,358
(Practicality puts Ha Yoon and her mother
on the same page.)

912
00:41:06,292 --> 00:41:11,931
(Only two choices remain.)

913
00:41:12,599 --> 00:41:15,168
(Will there be a new match?)

914
00:41:15,535 --> 00:41:19,172
(Or will the votes cluster again?)

915
00:41:19,505 --> 00:41:20,440
(Fourth to go, Lee Kang Hyeon's mother)

916
00:41:20,440 --> 00:41:24,244
I think Kang Hyeon's mother
might choose differently.

917
00:41:25,044 --> 00:41:27,413
When it comes to her daughter,

918
00:41:27,413 --> 00:41:29,415
- she's very levelheaded.
- Yes, she's very objective.

919
00:41:29,415 --> 00:41:31,651
She makes practical decisions.

920
00:41:32,886 --> 00:41:37,023
(Whom will
Lee Kang Hyeon's mother choose?)

921
00:41:37,357 --> 00:41:39,158
For today,

922
00:41:40,126 --> 00:41:42,328
I'd like to talk
with the doctor of Korean medicine.

923
00:41:42,328 --> 00:41:44,130
Every answer he gave...

924
00:41:44,130 --> 00:41:46,699
felt sincere...

925
00:41:46,699 --> 00:41:50,370
rather than rehearsed, and I liked that.

926
00:41:51,404 --> 00:41:55,208
(Kang Hyeon became interested in Shin Woo
after his introduction.)

927
00:41:55,208 --> 00:41:56,910
He really stood out to me.

928
00:41:57,477 --> 00:42:00,547
I had my heart set on him.

929
00:42:01,214 --> 00:42:02,782
This time, it's the mother's choice.

930
00:42:02,782 --> 00:42:04,417
Where will her mother go?

931
00:42:04,417 --> 00:42:06,686
(Who caught
Lee Kang Hyeon's mother's eye?)

932
00:42:11,057 --> 00:42:15,795
(She heads toward Seong Mo and Shin Woo.)

933
00:42:15,795 --> 00:42:16,763
The doctor of Korean medicine?

934
00:42:18,464 --> 00:42:22,769
(Will Kang Shin Woo receive another vote?)

935
00:42:26,406 --> 00:42:27,540
You were wrong.

936
00:42:28,541 --> 00:42:30,843
- She isn't so objective after all.
- Even she...

937
00:42:30,843 --> 00:42:32,345
She couldn't resist.

938
00:42:32,345 --> 00:42:35,381
Doctors of Korean medicine are popular
with the mothers.

939
00:42:35,381 --> 00:42:37,283
- Yes, they are.
- That's true.

940
00:42:37,283 --> 00:42:40,420
Just getting some moxibustion
and acupuncture,

941
00:42:40,420 --> 00:42:44,624
and having him prescribe you
some herbal medicine.

942
00:42:44,624 --> 00:42:46,526
Your own son-in-law
would be doing all that.

943
00:42:47,327 --> 00:42:48,428
That would be great.

944
00:42:48,428 --> 00:42:49,863
I should've studied harder.

945
00:42:49,863 --> 00:42:50,763
How great would that be?

946
00:42:52,632 --> 00:42:54,200
All the votes
are going to licensed professionals.

947
00:42:54,934 --> 00:42:56,536
Hurry and clap.

948
00:42:57,704 --> 00:42:58,671
Hello.

949
00:43:04,344 --> 00:43:05,278
Thank you.

950
00:43:05,845 --> 00:43:08,147
- My last name is also Kang.
- Thank you so much.

951
00:43:09,115 --> 00:43:10,350
Congratulations.

952
00:43:12,218 --> 00:43:13,386
Her hands are cold.

953
00:43:13,386 --> 00:43:14,787
My hands and feet are always cold.

954
00:43:14,787 --> 00:43:16,589
My son should take your pulse.

955
00:43:17,023 --> 00:43:19,192
(A welcome pulse-reading flirt)

956
00:43:19,192 --> 00:43:22,962
At first, I was interested in Seong Mo,

957
00:43:22,962 --> 00:43:27,166
but my interest dropped a little
because he's an athlete.

958
00:43:27,166 --> 00:43:31,704
Shin Woo seemed so warm,

959
00:43:31,704 --> 00:43:33,907
and I naturally felt drawn to him.

960
00:43:34,941 --> 00:43:36,442
This is the first time we've talked.

961
00:43:36,442 --> 00:43:39,145
I've wanted to talk to you too, but...

962
00:43:39,445 --> 00:43:40,580
But the timing never worked out.

963
00:43:40,580 --> 00:43:42,148
- Yes.
- That's right.

964
00:43:43,349 --> 00:43:45,518
The mothers are all together.

965
00:43:46,819 --> 00:43:47,720
(Kwon Ye Chan, 2 votes,
Kang Shin Woo, 2 votes)

966
00:43:47,720 --> 00:43:50,657
All four votes
went to licensed professionals.

967
00:43:50,657 --> 00:43:51,724
Exactly.

968
00:43:52,425 --> 00:43:54,627
What in the world is happening here?

969
00:43:54,627 --> 00:43:57,897
(Kim Dong Young, 0 votes)

970
00:43:57,897 --> 00:44:01,267
(Moon Seong Mo, 0 votes)

971
00:44:01,267 --> 00:44:03,603
I'm curious
where Jeong Yoon's mother will go.

972
00:44:03,970 --> 00:44:05,338
Jeong Yoon's mother.

973
00:44:05,572 --> 00:44:08,241
(Only Choi Jeong Yoon's
mother's choice remains.)

974
00:44:08,442 --> 00:44:10,010
Being last is not good.

975
00:44:12,746 --> 00:44:15,816
I paid closer attention
to about three of them.

976
00:44:15,816 --> 00:44:18,819
In Kwon also left an impression,

977
00:44:18,819 --> 00:44:24,191
and Ye Chan was about what I'd expected.

978
00:44:24,191 --> 00:44:27,695
Seong Mo seemed to have worked very hard
to get where he is.

979
00:44:27,695 --> 00:44:30,097
I didn't overthink it.

980
00:44:30,097 --> 00:44:33,501
I just chose the man
I wanted my daughter to talk to.

981
00:44:36,270 --> 00:44:38,806
I have a feeling
In Kwon will get her vote.

982
00:44:40,207 --> 00:44:42,409
Maybe...

983
00:44:42,409 --> 00:44:46,313
she regularly watches "Live Today"...

984
00:44:46,313 --> 00:44:48,115
and has grown fond of him.

985
00:44:51,218 --> 00:44:56,390
(Last to go, Choi Jeong Yoon's mother)

986
00:44:57,191 --> 00:45:02,763
(The mothers of the men
with zero votes are nervous.)

987
00:45:08,335 --> 00:45:10,738
I was torn between three men.

988
00:45:10,738 --> 00:45:14,842
But I wanted to start
with the man I know the least.

989
00:45:14,842 --> 00:45:18,045
The person I'd most like
to talk to is Ye Chan.

990
00:45:19,013 --> 00:45:24,018
(But both spots beside Ye Chan
are already taken.)

991
00:45:24,552 --> 00:45:29,790
(Will Jeong Yoon's mother's choice
match her daughter's?)

992
00:45:31,325 --> 00:45:32,059
(She passes Lee In Kwon.)

993
00:45:32,059 --> 00:45:33,360
Too bad, In Kwon.

994
00:45:34,261 --> 00:45:35,529
Is she passing him?

995
00:45:38,132 --> 00:45:41,902
(Where is she going
after passing In Kwon?)

996
00:45:41,902 --> 00:45:43,104
I think she'll go to Ye Chan.

997
00:45:43,104 --> 00:45:45,506
Will the lawyer get three votes again?

998
00:45:46,307 --> 00:45:50,744
(Or will she choose another candidate,
Moon Seong Mo?)

999
00:45:58,304 --> 00:46:00,173
(Eyes shut tight)

1000
00:46:00,173 --> 00:46:01,307
Is it here?

1001
00:46:02,308 --> 00:46:04,844
(She stops in front of Ye Chan.)

1002
00:46:05,144 --> 00:46:06,546
- Thank you.
- In the end...

1003
00:46:06,546 --> 00:46:07,947
He got three votes after all?

1004
00:46:08,615 --> 00:46:10,216
Again? Three votes, just like last season?

1005
00:46:10,216 --> 00:46:12,585
Just as we expected,

1006
00:46:12,585 --> 00:46:14,921
without the slightest surprise,

1007
00:46:14,921 --> 00:46:17,390
three for the lawyer,
two for the doctor. Done.

1008
00:46:17,991 --> 00:46:21,427
If she'd been trying to look good,
she'd have chosen someone else.

1009
00:46:21,427 --> 00:46:22,695
She genuinely chose him, thinking,

1010
00:46:22,695 --> 00:46:26,499
"I want this man as my son-in-law."

1011
00:46:26,499 --> 00:46:27,333
That's right.

1012
00:46:27,333 --> 00:46:28,635
And this is SBS, no less.

1013
00:46:28,635 --> 00:46:31,304
Even the SBS announcer got zero votes.

1014
00:46:31,304 --> 00:46:32,038
Yes.

1015
00:46:32,038 --> 00:46:34,440
- That's incredibly sincere.
- Absolutely.

1016
00:46:35,608 --> 00:46:36,709
I'll make her stand as close as possible.

1017
00:46:36,709 --> 00:46:37,710
Okay.

1018
00:46:37,710 --> 00:46:38,811
Where should I...

1019
00:46:38,811 --> 00:46:39,779
Thank you.

1020
00:46:46,953 --> 00:46:47,821
This is a problem.

1021
00:46:47,821 --> 00:46:48,855
What do we do?

1022
00:46:53,560 --> 00:46:54,460
What do we do?

1023
00:46:55,061 --> 00:46:57,030
(Kwon Ye Chan receives 3 votes
from the women's mothers.)

1024
00:46:57,030 --> 00:46:58,231
You must be happy.

1025
00:46:59,098 --> 00:47:02,735
I do tend to follow the crowd.

1026
00:47:02,735 --> 00:47:03,736
You're right.

1027
00:47:03,736 --> 00:47:07,173
(Jeong Yoon, Do Yoon, Ha Yoon,
a clean sweep of the three Yoons' mothers)

1028
00:47:07,407 --> 00:47:11,144
Thank you, Ms. Go.

1029
00:47:11,144 --> 00:47:12,545
My goodness.

1030
00:47:12,545 --> 00:47:14,948
There are three ladies.

1031
00:47:16,483 --> 00:47:19,719
I want to choose Kwon Ye Chan.

1032
00:47:20,019 --> 00:47:22,722
I think he could be a supportive,

1033
00:47:22,722 --> 00:47:25,859
friend-like partner
in Jeong Yoon's career.

1034
00:47:25,859 --> 00:47:29,796
He seems to have grown up
in a warm, happy family,

1035
00:47:29,796 --> 00:47:33,066
so I think he'd bring her
a sense of comfort.

1036
00:47:33,066 --> 00:47:37,136
That's one of those things
mothers really care about.

1037
00:47:37,136 --> 00:47:38,004
Of course.

1038
00:47:38,605 --> 00:47:40,673
You must be thrilled.

1039
00:47:40,673 --> 00:47:43,076
My heart is breaking.

1040
00:47:43,076 --> 00:47:44,677
- Just enjoy it.
- No.

1041
00:47:45,778 --> 00:47:47,814
The mothers are showering you with love.

1042
00:47:47,814 --> 00:47:49,015
Seriously.

1043
00:47:49,015 --> 00:47:50,884
You're the mothers' favorite.

1044
00:47:50,884 --> 00:47:51,818
I'm grateful.

1045
00:47:52,552 --> 00:47:53,653
That felt good.

1046
00:47:53,653 --> 00:47:55,421
"Thank you, past me."

1047
00:47:55,421 --> 00:47:56,656
That's what I thought.

1048
00:47:56,923 --> 00:48:03,263
It made me realize...

1049
00:48:03,263 --> 00:48:05,265
just how much the mothers' generation...

1050
00:48:05,265 --> 00:48:08,201
favors licensed professions.

1051
00:48:09,435 --> 00:48:11,137
You did a great job raising your son.

1052
00:48:12,805 --> 00:48:15,642
His popularity went up
after my introduction.

1053
00:48:15,642 --> 00:48:17,710
During my introduction,

1054
00:48:17,710 --> 00:48:20,046
I think I said the kind of things...

1055
00:48:20,046 --> 00:48:22,348
prospective daughters-in-law want to hear.

1056
00:48:22,348 --> 00:48:24,083
- Exactly.
- Don't you think?

1057
00:48:24,083 --> 00:48:24,818
Agreed.

1058
00:48:25,618 --> 00:48:26,786
(And the three men who received no votes)

1059
00:48:26,786 --> 00:48:30,657
In Kwon, Dong Young,
and Seong Mo all received zero votes.

1060
00:48:32,859 --> 00:48:33,860
Three men.

1061
00:48:36,095 --> 00:48:37,263
I received zero votes.

1062
00:48:38,198 --> 00:48:41,968
Walking out of there,
I wished I didn't have to go to work.

1063
00:48:42,635 --> 00:48:44,137
I was fine,

1064
00:48:44,370 --> 00:48:48,308
but seeing my mother
force a smile was harder.

1065
00:48:51,644 --> 00:48:54,781
For mothers,

1066
00:48:54,781 --> 00:48:58,685
there's still a desire
to match their daughters...

1067
00:48:58,685 --> 00:49:02,922
with stable professionals
like doctors or lawyers.

1068
00:49:02,922 --> 00:49:06,559
As a mother, I understand.

1069
00:49:09,095 --> 00:49:10,930
I'd expected it to some degree.

1070
00:49:10,930 --> 00:49:12,866
I thought the women's mothers...

1071
00:49:12,866 --> 00:49:14,601
would favor licensed professionals.

1072
00:49:14,601 --> 00:49:16,135
That was what I expected.

1073
00:49:19,506 --> 00:49:23,009
Dong Young is truly a wonderful person,

1074
00:49:23,009 --> 00:49:24,844
but it would be
a long-distance relationship.

1075
00:49:24,844 --> 00:49:28,414
Then a doctor of Korean medicine
and a lawyer entered the mix,

1076
00:49:28,414 --> 00:49:30,950
so I knew it wouldn't be easy.

1077
00:49:32,619 --> 00:49:38,258
My education isn't as impressive
as the other men's,

1078
00:49:38,258 --> 00:49:42,495
and careers matter a lot here.

1079
00:49:42,495 --> 00:49:46,533
Maybe the professional titles
won them over.

1080
00:49:46,533 --> 00:49:49,502
I tried to smile,

1081
00:49:49,502 --> 00:49:51,771
but Mom didn't.

1082
00:49:51,771 --> 00:49:53,239
How could she?

1083
00:49:53,773 --> 00:49:55,708
The others are great,

1084
00:49:55,708 --> 00:49:58,044
but so is my son.

1085
00:49:58,044 --> 00:49:59,712
Seong Mo worked incredibly hard...

1086
00:49:59,712 --> 00:50:01,714
to get where he is.

1087
00:50:01,714 --> 00:50:03,616
But what can we do?

1088
00:50:05,185 --> 00:50:09,956
One consolation was
that Seong Mo wasn't the only one.

1089
00:50:09,956 --> 00:50:12,859
A couple of other men were standing alone,

1090
00:50:12,859 --> 00:50:13,960
so I took comfort in that.

1091
00:50:16,696 --> 00:50:17,997
You did well, son.

1092
00:50:17,997 --> 00:50:19,599
It was hard standing there alone.

1093
00:50:19,933 --> 00:50:22,635
At least there were three of us.

1094
00:50:23,102 --> 00:50:24,137
Can't "announcer" count
as a licensed profession?

1095
00:50:24,137 --> 00:50:25,572
"Licensed announcer."

1096
00:50:25,572 --> 00:50:28,408
- Since they like licensed professionals.
- They like licensed professionals.

1097
00:50:28,408 --> 00:50:30,109
We should've said that before the vote.

1098
00:50:30,109 --> 00:50:31,678
Now it just sounds desperate.

1099
00:50:32,545 --> 00:50:35,114
- Let's get out of here.
- Let's go.

1100
00:50:35,582 --> 00:50:37,150
I didn't like those two anyway.

1101
00:50:38,051 --> 00:50:41,020
I think these two are the best, ma'am.

1102
00:50:41,821 --> 00:50:43,289
You have a spring in your step now.

1103
00:50:43,289 --> 00:50:44,390
I sure do.

1104
00:50:45,391 --> 00:50:47,994
Why did this...

1105
00:50:49,062 --> 00:50:51,431
- make us so nervous?
- It's the most important thing.

1106
00:50:51,431 --> 00:50:52,398
Is it?

1107
00:50:52,398 --> 00:50:53,533
In life.

1108
00:50:53,533 --> 00:50:57,237
Da Hye's mother's choice
really surprised me.

1109
00:50:57,237 --> 00:50:59,539
I didn't think she'd pick me.
I never saw it coming.

1110
00:50:59,539 --> 00:51:04,377
I thought she'd tell Da Hye
to talk to someone else too.

1111
00:51:05,311 --> 00:51:07,213
Yesterday, I showed...

1112
00:51:07,213 --> 00:51:10,250
- a heart. Maybe that made the difference.
- Right, you sent her a heart.

1113
00:51:10,250 --> 00:51:12,619
Did your strategy work?

1114
00:51:13,386 --> 00:51:15,655
Tomorrow, it's your turn to be chosen.

1115
00:51:16,089 --> 00:51:16,956
(Pick me.)

1116
00:51:16,956 --> 00:51:18,258
Right.

1117
00:51:18,258 --> 00:51:19,425
So that's why.

1118
00:51:19,425 --> 00:51:20,426
(His carefully planned heart
wins her over.)

1119
00:51:21,194 --> 00:51:23,463
It left an impression.

1120
00:51:24,297 --> 00:51:27,400
If you'd taken all the mothers' pulses,

1121
00:51:27,400 --> 00:51:29,202
you would've gotten four votes.

1122
00:51:29,435 --> 00:51:32,772
You look much more cheerful now.

1123
00:51:32,772 --> 00:51:34,474
You really do.

1124
00:51:35,408 --> 00:51:38,945
Shin Woo's mother seems
to have regained her pride.

1125
00:51:38,945 --> 00:51:40,980
She came in so proud,

1126
00:51:40,980 --> 00:51:42,482
then he didn't get any votes.

1127
00:51:42,482 --> 00:51:44,484
He got zero in the first-impression vote.

1128
00:51:44,484 --> 00:51:45,919
He wasn't chosen,

1129
00:51:45,919 --> 00:51:47,187
but today,

1130
00:51:47,187 --> 00:51:48,955
she seems to have recovered a little.

1131
00:51:48,955 --> 00:51:50,590
He received two votes, after all.

1132
00:51:50,824 --> 00:51:53,693
It's hot.

1133
00:51:54,194 --> 00:51:55,628
I said...

1134
00:51:55,628 --> 00:51:58,364
I wouldn't act
like a demanding mother-in-law,

1135
00:51:58,364 --> 00:51:59,899
and that's what made you
even more popular.

1136
00:51:59,899 --> 00:52:01,501
Mom, your introduction was excellent.

1137
00:52:01,501 --> 00:52:02,468
- It was.
- Seriously.

1138
00:52:03,436 --> 00:52:04,571
I definitely think so.

1139
00:52:04,571 --> 00:52:05,738
Yes, absolutely.

1140
00:52:06,739 --> 00:52:08,808
Have a good conversation.

1141
00:52:08,808 --> 00:52:09,709
Yes.

1142
00:52:10,810 --> 00:52:12,245
So you can...

1143
00:52:12,245 --> 00:52:13,112
I'm good at that.

1144
00:52:13,112 --> 00:52:15,982
Three women didn't throw me off at all.

1145
00:52:15,982 --> 00:52:16,783
Okay.

1146
00:52:16,783 --> 00:52:20,320
He's been so confident from the beginning.

1147
00:52:20,320 --> 00:52:21,654
But it really hit me.

1148
00:52:21,654 --> 00:52:22,422
What?

1149
00:52:23,356 --> 00:52:25,158
People really do care about careers.

1150
00:52:25,959 --> 00:52:28,428
I think so too.

1151
00:52:28,428 --> 00:52:30,964
I'm not just saying this
because you're my son.

1152
00:52:30,964 --> 00:52:33,399
You are a very desirable husband prospect.

1153
00:52:37,070 --> 00:52:38,204
Goodness.

1154
00:52:39,606 --> 00:52:42,709
It's okay.
If I had a daughter, I'd do the same.

1155
00:52:42,709 --> 00:52:43,643
Well...

1156
00:52:44,777 --> 00:52:47,280
Even if I were the mother of a daughter,
I'd choose a licensed professional too.

1157
00:52:48,281 --> 00:52:50,350
We just have to accept it.

1158
00:52:50,350 --> 00:52:53,153
There are clearly
certain careers mothers prefer.

1159
00:52:53,153 --> 00:52:56,890
Judging by the way the votes split,

1160
00:52:58,458 --> 00:53:00,226
- that's how it looks.
- Poor him.

1161
00:53:01,161 --> 00:53:04,264
With Dong Young, it isn't just his career.

1162
00:53:04,264 --> 00:53:07,467
The distance is a deal-breaker.

1163
00:53:07,467 --> 00:53:08,234
That's right.

1164
00:53:08,234 --> 00:53:10,870
Almost everyone else
seems to live in Seoul.

1165
00:53:10,870 --> 00:53:11,771
Exactly.

1166
00:53:12,605 --> 00:53:13,940
There's nothing we can do now.

1167
00:53:14,574 --> 00:53:15,909
Get to know Da Hye once more, and then...

1168
00:53:15,909 --> 00:53:16,743
What about Ha Yoon?

1169
00:53:16,743 --> 00:53:20,313
No, I feel like Ha Yoon
has already made her choice.

1170
00:53:23,049 --> 00:53:24,150
- Really?
- Yes.

1171
00:53:24,818 --> 00:53:26,052
Dong Young.

1172
00:53:26,719 --> 00:53:27,821
It's okay.

1173
00:53:28,988 --> 00:53:32,192
Ha Yoon chose someone else, after all.

1174
00:53:32,192 --> 00:53:35,929
So I have a strong feeling
it won't work out.

1175
00:53:35,929 --> 00:53:37,363
It won't be easy.

1176
00:53:38,298 --> 00:53:41,501
Still, I'm so grateful you're not alone.

1177
00:53:41,935 --> 00:53:43,369
Dong Young, did you leave for a date?

1178
00:53:43,369 --> 00:53:44,337
No.

1179
00:53:44,871 --> 00:53:45,972
I thought you'd gone somewhere.

1180
00:53:47,140 --> 00:53:50,743
(The fellow zero-vote men
take comfort in one another.)

1181
00:53:50,743 --> 00:53:53,680
With three in the same boat,
it must feel less lonely.

1182
00:53:55,815 --> 00:53:56,816
Honestly, after watching Season One,

1183
00:53:56,816 --> 00:53:58,318
I came here thinking...

1184
00:53:58,318 --> 00:54:00,820
I had a fighting chance.

1185
00:54:00,820 --> 00:54:02,222
But it's completely different.

1186
00:54:03,089 --> 00:54:04,057
So much has changed.

1187
00:54:04,057 --> 00:54:04,824
Anybody there?

1188
00:54:05,458 --> 00:54:06,292
Seriously?

1189
00:54:07,427 --> 00:54:08,228
Seriously?

1190
00:54:08,228 --> 00:54:09,195
Goodness.

1191
00:54:09,195 --> 00:54:10,296
(Showing off his ripped back)

1192
00:54:10,296 --> 00:54:12,599
Hey, you should go on "Single's Inferno"...

1193
00:54:12,599 --> 00:54:14,133
if you're going to do that.

1194
00:54:14,133 --> 00:54:17,103
Isn't it a bit much?
You're here for matchmaking.

1195
00:54:17,103 --> 00:54:18,605
I'm not getting anywhere here either.

1196
00:54:18,605 --> 00:54:20,240
Ma'am, please tell him off.

1197
00:54:20,240 --> 00:54:21,641
But...

1198
00:54:21,641 --> 00:54:24,010
he's always like that. There's no point.

1199
00:54:24,010 --> 00:54:25,578
It's so hot.

1200
00:54:25,578 --> 00:54:28,982
And I have makeup on.

1201
00:54:28,982 --> 00:54:31,818
You really belong on "Single's Inferno,"
not here.

1202
00:54:31,818 --> 00:54:33,286
Exactly. He should be there.

1203
00:54:33,286 --> 00:54:34,454
He came to the wrong place.

1204
00:54:36,322 --> 00:54:39,859
Why didn't any of the mothers
choose Seong Mo?

1205
00:54:39,859 --> 00:54:45,131
Maybe they think
his career is less stable...

1206
00:54:45,698 --> 00:54:47,400
since he gives lessons.

1207
00:54:48,601 --> 00:54:50,403
- You're torn between three men?
- Yes.

1208
00:54:51,538 --> 00:54:54,474
After hearing the introductions,

1209
00:54:54,474 --> 00:54:56,943
they all moved closer together
in my rankings.

1210
00:54:56,943 --> 00:54:58,044
Because...

1211
00:54:58,044 --> 00:54:59,879
I really liked In Kwon,

1212
00:54:59,879 --> 00:55:03,249
but he turned out to be a broadcaster,
which gives me pause.

1213
00:55:03,249 --> 00:55:06,219
Faith was extremely important to Ye Chan,

1214
00:55:06,219 --> 00:55:08,254
and I don't share his faith.

1215
00:55:08,254 --> 00:55:11,457
Seong Mo is a professional golfer,

1216
00:55:11,457 --> 00:55:14,894
and I vaguely thought it might be hard...

1217
00:55:14,894 --> 00:55:16,362
to adjust to his lifestyle.

1218
00:55:17,430 --> 00:55:19,465
It's a good thing
I didn't take you to Ye Chan.

1219
00:55:19,899 --> 00:55:21,868
Look how many women are with Ye Chan.

1220
00:55:21,868 --> 00:55:22,702
Exactly.

1221
00:55:23,236 --> 00:55:27,707
Ye Chan and Shin Woo
were my first and second choices.

1222
00:55:27,707 --> 00:55:29,142
I thought you could get to know
Ye Chan better.

1223
00:55:29,142 --> 00:55:31,544
I truly meant to go to Ye Chan...

1224
00:55:31,544 --> 00:55:33,046
because they're a family of faith.

1225
00:55:33,046 --> 00:55:34,714
Right. That means a lot.

1226
00:55:34,714 --> 00:55:36,950
I want to talk to him more too.

1227
00:55:36,950 --> 00:55:40,420
Right.
Faith is important to Da Hye's family too.

1228
00:55:40,420 --> 00:55:42,622
But I'm most worried about the dog.

1229
00:55:42,622 --> 00:55:44,324
We need to ask about that. Please do.

1230
00:55:44,924 --> 00:55:48,027
Mom, I'm sorry,

1231
00:55:48,027 --> 00:55:50,463
but I want a dog. That's what matters.

1232
00:55:50,463 --> 00:55:52,265
You're not the one
who's going to live with Shin Woo.

1233
00:55:52,265 --> 00:55:53,266
Even if I end up with him,

1234
00:55:53,266 --> 00:55:55,535
I'll be the one living with my husband.

1235
00:55:55,535 --> 00:55:57,570
So why are you worried about the dog?

1236
00:55:57,570 --> 00:55:58,438
When you have a baby...

1237
00:55:58,438 --> 00:56:00,106
I'm going to raise a dog
and a baby together.

1238
00:56:00,106 --> 00:56:03,910
- You can't, with fur everywhere.
- Her mother says she can't.

1239
00:56:03,910 --> 00:56:05,778
I'm absolutely going to.

1240
00:56:05,778 --> 00:56:07,680
I said an outdoor dog is fine.

1241
00:56:09,499 --> 00:56:12,368
If you live in a big hanok
and let the dog roam outside,

1242
00:56:12,368 --> 00:56:13,503
I'd even come by to help.

1243
00:56:15,238 --> 00:56:17,707
She's already thinking that far ahead.

1244
00:56:17,707 --> 00:56:19,142
Her daughter will get married,

1245
00:56:19,142 --> 00:56:21,577
and she'll have to visit their home.

1246
00:56:21,577 --> 00:56:23,646
She's already worried
that a dog would make visits too hard.

1247
00:56:23,646 --> 00:56:25,715
That's how far ahead she's thinking.

1248
00:56:26,115 --> 00:56:28,317
I just can't get past the dog.

1249
00:56:28,684 --> 00:56:30,920
They may have children after they marry,

1250
00:56:30,920 --> 00:56:33,956
and I worry about allergies
and things like that.

1251
00:56:33,956 --> 00:56:36,559
It just makes me uneasy.

1252
00:56:37,193 --> 00:56:39,028
I'm exhausted.

1253
00:56:39,028 --> 00:56:40,563
This is so hard.

1254
00:56:40,563 --> 00:56:42,832
It's incredibly emotionally draining.

1255
00:56:42,832 --> 00:56:43,866
That was hard, wasn't it, Mom?

1256
00:56:43,866 --> 00:56:46,002
Yes, it was so hard, Ha Yoon.

1257
00:56:46,002 --> 00:56:48,471
I knew you'd choose Ye Chan.

1258
00:56:48,471 --> 00:56:51,107
He'd been
your one and only pick all along.

1259
00:56:51,107 --> 00:56:53,710
And you love...

1260
00:56:53,710 --> 00:56:56,012
that he lives nearby
and you can see him often.

1261
00:56:56,012 --> 00:56:58,715
So I knew you'd choose Ye Chan.

1262
00:56:58,715 --> 00:56:59,582
Really?

1263
00:56:59,582 --> 00:57:00,483
But...

1264
00:57:00,483 --> 00:57:03,986
the question now is whom I will choose.

1265
00:57:03,986 --> 00:57:05,688
I really...

1266
00:57:06,489 --> 00:57:07,957
If only he lived as far as Busan...

1267
00:57:07,957 --> 00:57:10,526
Busan is a quick KTX ride away.

1268
00:57:10,526 --> 00:57:12,562
Exactly. If only it were Busan.

1269
00:57:12,929 --> 00:57:14,464
But Gimhae is too far.

1270
00:57:14,464 --> 00:57:16,232
- It's too far.
- Far too far.

1271
00:57:17,200 --> 00:57:21,070
But if Dong Young's feelings
grow stronger here,

1272
00:57:21,070 --> 00:57:24,107
and both of us become certain
about each other,

1273
00:57:24,107 --> 00:57:25,842
if we decide we could get married,

1274
00:57:25,842 --> 00:57:30,179
with someone like Dong Young,

1275
00:57:30,179 --> 00:57:32,515
I think he'd move to Seoul.

1276
00:57:32,515 --> 00:57:33,383
That's what he said today.

1277
00:57:33,383 --> 00:57:36,552
He said he'd go anywhere
south of the 38th parallel.

1278
00:57:36,552 --> 00:57:38,955
I honestly believe he would.

1279
00:57:38,955 --> 00:57:41,424
I don't think those were empty words.

1280
00:57:41,424 --> 00:57:42,658
Still...

1281
00:57:42,658 --> 00:57:43,793
They weren't empty words.

1282
00:57:43,793 --> 00:57:44,861
But what?

1283
00:57:44,861 --> 00:57:46,062
However,

1284
00:57:46,062 --> 00:57:47,296
in my view,

1285
00:57:47,296 --> 00:57:49,832
I've been around a long time, right?

1286
00:57:49,832 --> 00:57:54,070
Walking away from a life you've spent
years building isn't easy.

1287
00:57:54,070 --> 00:57:56,139
How can he leave it all behind?

1288
00:57:58,441 --> 00:58:00,777
You need to meet someone
you can marry now.

1289
00:58:09,986 --> 00:58:11,754
- Let's go have fun.
- That sounds good.

1290
00:58:11,754 --> 00:58:14,390
But you must feel
a lot of pressure on your shoulders.

1291
00:58:15,324 --> 00:58:16,459
I'm just grateful.

1292
00:58:16,459 --> 00:58:17,827
He's the king of the ladies of Season Two.

1293
00:58:17,827 --> 00:58:19,328
That's true.

1294
00:58:19,762 --> 00:58:21,431
This is basically the Ye Chan special.

1295
00:58:21,431 --> 00:58:22,598
Not at all.

1296
00:58:22,598 --> 00:58:24,100
- The king of the ladies.
- Thank you.

1297
00:58:25,034 --> 00:58:27,103
A three-on-one date isn't
necessarily all fun.

1298
00:58:27,103 --> 00:58:29,138
Right. It's not all good.

1299
00:58:29,138 --> 00:58:31,974
I have a question.

1300
00:58:31,974 --> 00:58:36,446
Earlier, you said
you were interested in three women.

1301
00:58:37,680 --> 00:58:40,183
How many women are you drawn to right now?

1302
00:58:40,183 --> 00:58:41,250
Three.

1303
00:58:42,822 --> 00:58:46,367
You said you were interested
in three women.

1304
00:58:46,367 --> 00:58:47,668
Are they these three right here?

1305
00:58:47,698 --> 00:58:49,934
Just say it's those three.

1306
00:58:49,934 --> 00:58:50,901
She's very direct.

1307
00:58:50,901 --> 00:58:52,036
Almost all of them are here.

1308
00:58:52,036 --> 00:58:54,338
- Almost all?
- I see.

1309
00:58:54,338 --> 00:58:55,639
Almost all?

1310
00:58:57,708 --> 00:58:59,677
That's a very careful answer.

1311
00:58:59,677 --> 00:59:00,644
Seriously.

1312
00:59:00,644 --> 00:59:01,946
Spoken like a lawyer.

1313
00:59:02,980 --> 00:59:04,215
Indeed.

1314
00:59:05,216 --> 00:59:07,218
How should we sit? Wherever we want?

1315
00:59:07,218 --> 00:59:08,919
There's the seating arrangement.

1316
00:59:08,919 --> 00:59:10,187
Exactly.

1317
00:59:10,187 --> 00:59:11,822
Does anyone want the front seat?

1318
00:59:11,822 --> 00:59:13,491
- Eldest first.
- Really?

1319
00:59:13,491 --> 00:59:15,192
- Eldest first.
- Really?

1320
00:59:16,060 --> 00:59:19,397
Your ankle hurts, so take the front.

1321
00:59:19,397 --> 00:59:20,331
Goodness.

1322
00:59:20,331 --> 00:59:21,365
All right.

1323
00:59:21,365 --> 00:59:22,533
Thank you.

1324
00:59:22,533 --> 00:59:23,734
I can't believe this.

1325
00:59:23,734 --> 00:59:25,136
At least there are three of them.

1326
00:59:25,136 --> 00:59:26,871
Two would've been awkward.

1327
00:59:28,205 --> 00:59:29,440
Let's have another good date today.

1328
00:59:29,440 --> 00:59:30,675
Yes, let's.

1329
00:59:32,209 --> 00:59:35,479
(Ha Yoon and Ye Chan go on a date again.)

1330
00:59:35,479 --> 00:59:37,882
You have three women to look after today.

1331
00:59:37,882 --> 00:59:39,984
So I'm really trying to stay focused.

1332
00:59:41,318 --> 00:59:43,320
You said you commute by car, right?

1333
00:59:43,320 --> 00:59:44,588
Yes, that's right.

1334
00:59:44,588 --> 00:59:45,756
Since I'm based in Gwangju.

1335
00:59:45,756 --> 00:59:48,025
This feels nice and easy.

1336
00:59:48,025 --> 00:59:50,161
Yesterday, the conversation kept stalling
at moments like this.

1337
00:59:50,161 --> 00:59:51,162
That's right.

1338
00:59:52,396 --> 00:59:55,499
So where did you serve
during those three years?

1339
00:59:55,499 --> 00:59:57,601
I spent my first year
in Gwangju, Jeolla Province.

1340
00:59:57,601 --> 01:00:00,871
At the Korea Legal Aid Corporation.

1341
01:00:00,871 --> 01:00:03,374
Then my second year was in Daejeon.

1342
01:00:03,374 --> 01:00:04,475
Where in Daejeon?

1343
01:00:05,476 --> 01:00:06,677
I'm from Daejeon.

1344
01:00:06,677 --> 01:00:07,511
Really?

1345
01:00:07,511 --> 01:00:09,013
Until I turned 20, I lived there.

1346
01:00:09,013 --> 01:00:10,848
I lived in Dunsan-dong
near the courthouse.

1347
01:00:10,848 --> 01:00:12,850
- I'm from Dunsan-dong.
- Really?

1348
01:00:12,850 --> 01:00:14,051
In front of the Government Complex.

1349
01:00:14,051 --> 01:00:15,353
I was right beside it.

1350
01:00:15,353 --> 01:00:16,687
I lived in an apartment there.

1351
01:00:16,687 --> 01:00:17,955
Another...

1352
01:00:17,955 --> 01:00:21,025
- thing in common.
- They keep finding common ground.

1353
01:00:21,025 --> 01:00:22,927
So that's why you were Miss Korea Daejeon.

1354
01:00:22,927 --> 01:00:24,695
That's right. I represented Daejeon.

1355
01:00:24,695 --> 01:00:26,130
I see.

1356
01:00:29,133 --> 01:00:31,736
This looks delicious. Let's eat.

1357
01:00:32,036 --> 01:00:34,672
(Ye Chan starts setting the table.)

1358
01:00:34,672 --> 01:00:35,740
Thank you.

1359
01:00:36,741 --> 01:00:37,675
Thank you.

1360
01:00:38,676 --> 01:00:39,744
Thank you.

1361
01:00:41,278 --> 01:00:42,580
You said you wanted pizza earlier, right?

1362
01:00:42,580 --> 01:00:43,514
That's right.

1363
01:00:44,682 --> 01:00:46,650
(The popular man is busy
taking care of all three.)

1364
01:00:46,650 --> 01:00:47,718
Thank you.

1365
01:00:48,552 --> 01:00:49,553
(The same service for everyone)

1366
01:00:49,553 --> 01:00:51,756
He's really good at that.

1367
01:00:52,423 --> 01:00:54,225
You're doing your best.

1368
01:00:54,225 --> 01:00:55,359
I need to do everything I can.

1369
01:00:56,460 --> 01:00:59,130
Funny enough,
all three of our names end in "Yoon."

1370
01:00:59,130 --> 01:00:59,997
Right.

1371
01:00:59,997 --> 01:01:01,565
We have a lot in common.

1372
01:01:01,565 --> 01:01:03,367
So I'm very nervous.

1373
01:01:03,367 --> 01:01:05,603
One mistake could ruin everything.

1374
01:01:06,170 --> 01:01:09,273
Now that everyone's profiles are out,

1375
01:01:09,273 --> 01:01:11,909
have your feelings changed much?

1376
01:01:11,909 --> 01:01:13,144
After hearing the introductions.

1377
01:01:14,612 --> 01:01:16,881
Not dramatically.

1378
01:01:16,881 --> 01:01:19,383
Did anything change
for the men since yesterday?

1379
01:01:19,383 --> 01:01:20,818
As I said earlier,

1380
01:01:20,818 --> 01:01:23,421
there about three women
I was interested in.

1381
01:01:23,421 --> 01:01:25,089
Those three stayed the same,

1382
01:01:25,890 --> 01:01:28,793
but second and third place
switched slightly.

1383
01:01:28,793 --> 01:01:30,094
So it wasn't a big change.

1384
01:01:30,795 --> 01:01:34,999
My mother's top choice
was Ye Chan from the beginning.

1385
01:01:34,999 --> 01:01:37,068
Out of nowhere.

1386
01:01:37,068 --> 01:01:38,302
Out of nowhere?

1387
01:01:38,302 --> 01:01:39,570
She said he was her type.

1388
01:01:40,204 --> 01:01:41,605
Her type?

1389
01:01:41,605 --> 01:01:43,007
She said he was very handsome.

1390
01:01:43,741 --> 01:01:45,109
I'm flattered.

1391
01:01:45,109 --> 01:01:47,311
Through her mother,

1392
01:01:47,311 --> 01:01:50,014
she's flirting.

1393
01:01:53,417 --> 01:01:54,352
How do you usually eat lunch?

1394
01:01:54,352 --> 01:01:56,754
Alone or with others?

1395
01:01:56,754 --> 01:01:58,055
Usually with my team.

1396
01:01:58,055 --> 01:01:59,056
Every day?

1397
01:01:59,056 --> 01:02:00,858
Yes, always.

1398
01:02:00,858 --> 01:02:03,361
- I eat alone.
- You eat alone?

1399
01:02:03,361 --> 01:02:06,797
You seem like a true introvert.

1400
01:02:06,797 --> 01:02:07,965
That's right.

1401
01:02:07,965 --> 01:02:09,934
So do you prefer dates at home?

1402
01:02:09,934 --> 01:02:11,802
I like staying in,

1403
01:02:11,802 --> 01:02:13,170
or just hanging out
around the neighborhood.

1404
01:02:13,170 --> 01:02:16,574
I like keeping things casual.
That way, we can meet more often.

1405
01:02:16,574 --> 01:02:17,541
Right.

1406
01:02:18,609 --> 01:02:19,744
Do you read a lot?

1407
01:02:19,744 --> 01:02:22,480
Yes. I mainly read about my work.

1408
01:02:22,480 --> 01:02:25,950
Dieting or meal plans.

1409
01:02:25,950 --> 01:02:27,618
She's a total STEM person.

1410
01:02:27,618 --> 01:02:28,853
I majored in electronics engineering.

1411
01:02:28,853 --> 01:02:30,988
You must've been popular in that major.

1412
01:02:30,988 --> 01:02:33,224
- In college?
- With all the guys.

1413
01:02:33,224 --> 01:02:36,027
And you got a job
before graduating, right?

1414
01:02:36,027 --> 01:02:36,827
That's right.

1415
01:02:36,827 --> 01:02:38,496
The mood is great.

1416
01:02:38,496 --> 01:02:40,765
Everyone is getting equal time.

1417
01:02:40,765 --> 01:02:44,235
He's dividing the airtime
perfectly evenly.

1418
01:02:44,235 --> 01:02:47,071
What an excellent host.

1419
01:02:47,772 --> 01:02:50,975
How do you handle conflict?

1420
01:02:50,975 --> 01:02:52,643
I like to resolve things right away too.

1421
01:02:52,643 --> 01:02:55,680
What kind of person do you like?

1422
01:02:55,680 --> 01:02:58,582
I used to only like people
who were my opposite.

1423
01:02:58,582 --> 01:02:59,417
Especially...

1424
01:02:59,417 --> 01:03:01,385
Overall, I think the atmosphere was good.

1425
01:03:01,385 --> 01:03:02,586
For my part,

1426
01:03:02,586 --> 01:03:06,323
I paid close attention
to giving all three women...

1427
01:03:06,624 --> 01:03:08,392
an equal share of the conversation.

1428
01:03:08,826 --> 01:03:12,063
You have to keep track of it constantly.

1429
01:03:12,063 --> 01:03:15,199
Without realizing it,
if you like someone more,

1430
01:03:15,199 --> 01:03:18,402
- you keep...
- You're curious and ask more questions.

1431
01:03:18,402 --> 01:03:21,138
But he avoided that
and treated everyone equally.

1432
01:03:21,138 --> 01:03:22,740
Handled like a true lawyer.

1433
01:03:24,542 --> 01:03:25,376
(Meanwhile, Shin Woo's team with 2 votes)

1434
01:03:25,376 --> 01:03:26,677
I'll sit on the inside.

1435
01:03:27,878 --> 01:03:29,246
This feels like an interview.

1436
01:03:30,381 --> 01:03:31,115
(It somehow turns
into a two-on-one interview.)

1437
01:03:31,115 --> 01:03:32,216
I feel like I'm being interviewed.

1438
01:03:33,851 --> 01:03:34,885
A stress interview.

1439
01:03:36,253 --> 01:03:38,756
We could grill you from head to toe.

1440
01:03:40,324 --> 01:03:42,360
(Already dazed)

1441
01:03:42,360 --> 01:03:43,427
- I'm kidding.
- Kang Hyeon.

1442
01:03:43,427 --> 01:03:46,163
I tend to lead the conversation...

1443
01:03:46,163 --> 01:03:48,966
to find out who someone really is.

1444
01:03:48,966 --> 01:03:51,635
That's what I want to know
about you right now, Shin Woo.

1445
01:03:52,036 --> 01:03:54,038
(The stress interview begins in earnest.
Gulp)

1446
01:03:54,038 --> 01:03:54,772
I'm sorry.

1447
01:03:54,772 --> 01:03:56,107
I'm not good with open-ended questions.

1448
01:03:56,107 --> 01:03:58,776
- I'm not trying to pressure you.
- No, I don't feel pressured.

1449
01:03:58,776 --> 01:04:00,511
What would you like to ask me?

1450
01:04:00,511 --> 01:04:01,979
- Right here, right now?
- Yes.

1451
01:04:01,979 --> 01:04:03,314
But there are two of us and one of you.

1452
01:04:03,314 --> 01:04:04,849
You need a one-on-one conversation
before you can ask?

1453
01:04:04,849 --> 01:04:06,717
Perfect timing, actually.

1454
01:04:06,717 --> 01:04:07,852
I really need to use the restroom.

1455
01:04:07,852 --> 01:04:10,321
- No.
- I've honestly been holding it in.

1456
01:04:10,321 --> 01:04:11,455
I'll be right back.

1457
01:04:11,455 --> 01:04:14,158
- She tactfully gave them space.
- Da Hye did.

1458
01:04:14,158 --> 01:04:16,727
Before my mother introduced me,

1459
01:04:16,727 --> 01:04:19,296
I planned to meet and talk
with different people.

1460
01:04:19,296 --> 01:04:21,866
But during the introduction,
you singled out one woman.

1461
01:04:21,866 --> 01:04:22,967
So honestly, I wondered...

1462
01:04:22,967 --> 01:04:25,069
whether I should even be
on this date today.

1463
01:04:25,669 --> 01:04:27,171
I'm interested in one woman.

1464
01:04:32,977 --> 01:04:34,512
But you don't know who she is.

1465
01:04:34,512 --> 01:04:35,813
I do know.

1466
01:04:35,813 --> 01:04:36,981
How do you know?

1467
01:04:37,314 --> 01:04:40,317
Shin Woo, you only ever chose her.

1468
01:04:40,317 --> 01:04:41,886
So you all know?

1469
01:04:41,886 --> 01:04:43,554
- It's obvious.
- What do you mean, how would she know?

1470
01:04:43,554 --> 01:04:44,822
It's obvious.

1471
01:04:44,822 --> 01:04:46,123
It's very obvious.

1472
01:04:46,123 --> 01:04:50,428
I've realized that once I choose someone,

1473
01:04:50,428 --> 01:04:51,762
I find it hard to change my mind.

1474
01:04:51,762 --> 01:04:54,165
I'm the type to stick with it.

1475
01:04:54,932 --> 01:04:55,966
But...

1476
01:04:55,966 --> 01:04:58,202
I'm not completely closed off.

1477
01:04:58,202 --> 01:04:59,170
You're not?

1478
01:04:59,170 --> 01:05:00,771
I'm not closed off to the others.

1479
01:05:00,771 --> 01:05:03,174
I'll talk with the other women...

1480
01:05:03,174 --> 01:05:04,542
and think about it further.

1481
01:05:05,276 --> 01:05:08,646
But I should be honest
about how I feel right now.

1482
01:05:08,646 --> 01:05:10,715
Of course. I appreciate that.

1483
01:05:12,583 --> 01:05:13,918
Enjoy your meal.

1484
01:05:13,918 --> 01:05:14,785
Enjoy.

1485
01:05:14,785 --> 01:05:15,953
Enjoy.

1486
01:05:17,254 --> 01:05:19,757
Shin Woo, you said you like food pairings.

1487
01:05:19,757 --> 01:05:23,294
What would you pair with this?

1488
01:05:23,294 --> 01:05:25,429
These dishes are quite strongly seasoned,

1489
01:05:25,429 --> 01:05:29,600
so a red wine would pair well.

1490
01:05:29,600 --> 01:05:32,937
But we can't drink. We're driving, right?

1491
01:05:32,937 --> 01:05:34,839
Do you enjoy drinking, though?

1492
01:05:34,839 --> 01:05:36,440
I do enjoy it.

1493
01:05:36,440 --> 01:05:37,708
I enjoy it.

1494
01:05:37,708 --> 01:05:39,543
- You enjoy drinking?
- Yes.

1495
01:05:40,378 --> 01:05:43,414
What makes you
see someone romantically, Shin Woo?

1496
01:05:43,781 --> 01:05:45,182
(Kang Hyeon's barrage
of questions begins.)

1497
01:05:45,182 --> 01:05:46,617
What is your mother like, Shin Woo?

1498
01:05:46,617 --> 01:05:47,418
My goodness.

1499
01:05:47,418 --> 01:05:48,252
My mother?

1500
01:05:48,252 --> 01:05:50,021
In what sense?

1501
01:05:50,021 --> 01:05:51,489
In every sense.

1502
01:05:51,489 --> 01:05:53,391
We don't know her,

1503
01:05:53,391 --> 01:05:55,793
so tell us what she's like.

1504
01:05:55,793 --> 01:05:57,028
It was almost an interrogation.

1505
01:05:57,028 --> 01:06:00,031
"How was it? What's that?"
She kept asking.

1506
01:06:00,031 --> 01:06:02,333
I felt like I was in a stress interview.

1507
01:06:02,333 --> 01:06:03,067
I see.

1508
01:06:03,067 --> 01:06:04,101
It was exhausting.

1509
01:06:04,635 --> 01:06:06,137
Eating with a woman I like...

1510
01:06:06,937 --> 01:06:08,105
and a woman I don't.

1511
01:06:08,105 --> 01:06:09,440
"A woman I don't."

1512
01:06:09,740 --> 01:06:13,344
It was my first time having a meal
with both at once.

1513
01:06:13,344 --> 01:06:15,346
The whole situation
was really uncomfortable.

1514
01:06:16,580 --> 01:06:17,782
I must have been very stressed.

1515
01:06:17,782 --> 01:06:18,883
A lot of mental stress.

1516
01:06:18,883 --> 01:06:21,352
My son is now known
as the man who goes all in.

1517
01:06:21,619 --> 01:06:24,288
(The contestants' feelings
grow more complicated after the dates.)

1518
01:06:24,288 --> 01:06:25,790
Why?

1519
01:06:25,890 --> 01:06:27,124
(The mothers begin
their serious inquiries.)

1520
01:06:27,124 --> 01:06:29,226
Where would you live?

1521
01:06:29,226 --> 01:06:31,762
Are you open
to a long-distance relationship?

1522
01:06:31,762 --> 01:06:33,464
This is driving me crazy.

1523
01:06:33,731 --> 01:06:36,033
All the mothers have gone out.

1524
01:06:36,033 --> 01:06:37,368
They have free time.

1525
01:06:37,368 --> 01:06:38,836
Can we talk for a minute?

1526
01:06:38,836 --> 01:06:39,737
Knock, knock.

1527
01:06:39,737 --> 01:06:41,605
- Who is it?
- It's Da Hye.

1528
01:06:41,605 --> 01:06:43,674
- Is Ye Chan there?
- Yes.

1529
01:06:43,674 --> 01:06:45,209
I really hate feeling like
I'm stealing someone away, though.

1530
01:06:46,277 --> 01:06:47,244
My goodness.

1531
01:06:47,244 --> 01:06:49,980
Am I one of your top choices?

1532
01:06:49,980 --> 01:06:52,183
He really is the king of the ladies.

1533
01:06:52,183 --> 01:06:54,051
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
